B040C009V010	40	9	10	And while He was reclining at table, a large number of tax-gathers and notorious sinners were of the party with Jesus and His disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	The Pharisees noticed this, and they inquired of His disciples, »Why does your Teacher eat with the tax-gatherers and notorious sinners?«
B040C009V012	40	9	12	He heard the question and replied, »It is not men in good health who require a doctor, but the sick.
B040C009V013	40	9	13	But go and learn what this means, 
B040C009V014	40	9	14	At that time John's disciples came and asked Jesus, »Why do we and the Pharisees fast, but your disciples do not?«
B040C009V015	40	9	15	»Can the bridegroom's party mourn,« He replied, »as long as the bridegroom is with them? But other days will come (when the Bridegroom has been taken from them) and then they will fast.
B040C009V016	40	9	16	No one ever mends an old cloak with a patch of newly woven cloth. Otherwise, the patch put on would tear away some of the old, and a worse hole would be made.
B040C009V017	40	9	17	Nor do people pour new wine into old wineskins. Otherwise, the skins would split, the wine would escape, and the skins be destroyed. But they put new wine into fresh skins, and both are saved.«
B040C009V018	40	9	18	While He was thus speaking, a Ruler came up and profoundly bowing said, »My daughter is just dead; but come and put your hand upon her and she will return to life.«
B040C009V019	40	9	19	And Jesus rose and followed him, as did also His disciples.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	But a woman who for twelve years had been afflicted with haemorrhage came behind Him and touched the tassel of His cloak;
B040C009V021	40	9	21	for she said to herself, »If I but touch His cloak, I shall be cured.«
B040C009V022	40	9	22	And Jesus turned and saw her, and said, »Take courage, daughter; your faith has cured you.« And the woman was restored to health from that moment.
B040C009V023	40	9	23	Entering the Ruler's house, Jesus saw the flute-players and the crowd loudly wailing,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	and He said, »Go out of the room; the little girl is not dead, but asleep.« And they laughed at Him.
B040C009V025	40	9	25	When however the place was cleared of the crowd, Jesus went in, and on His taking the little girl by the hand, she rose up.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	And the report of this spread throughout all that district.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	As Jesus passed on, two blind men followed Him, shouting and saying, »Pity us, Son of David.«
B040C009V028	40	9	28	And when He had gone indoors, they came to Him. »Do you believe that I can do this?« He asked them. »Yes, Sir,« they replied.
B040C009V029	40	9	29	So He touched their eyes and said, »According to your faith let it be to you.«
B040C009V030	40	9	30	Then their eyes were opened. And assuming a stern tone Jesus said to them, »Be careful to let no one know.«
B040C009V031	40	9	31	But they went out and published His fame in all that district.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	And as they were leaving His presence a dumb demoniac was brought to Him.
B040C009V033	40	9	33	When the demon was expelled, the dumb man could speak. And the crowds exclaimed in astonishment, »Never was such a thing seen in Israel.«
B040C009V034	40	9	34	But the Pharisees maintained, »It is by the power of the Prince of the demons that he drives out the demons.«
B040C009V035	40	9	35	And Jesus continued His circuits through all the towns and the villages, teaching in their synagogues and proclaiming the Good News of the Kingdom, and curing every kind of disease and infirmity.
B040C009V036	40	9	36	And when He saw the crowds He was touched with pity for them, because they were distressed and were fainting on the ground like sheep which have no shepherd.
B040C009V037	40	9	37	Then He said to His disciples, »The harvest is abundant, but the reapers are few;
B040C009V038	40	9	38	therefore entreat the Owner of the Harvest to send out reapers into His fields.«
B040C010V001	40	10	1	Then He called to Him His twelve disciples and gave them authority over foul spirits, to drive them out; and to cure every kind of disease and infirmity.
B040C010V002	40	10	2	Now the names of the twelve Apostles were these: first, Simon called Peter, and his brother Andrew; James the son of Zabdi, and his brother John;
B040C010V003	40	10	3	Philip and Bartholomew, Thomas and Matthew the tax-gatherer, James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus;
B040C010V004	40	10	4	Simon the Cananaean, and Judas the Iscariot, who also betrayed Him.
B040C010V005	40	10	5	These twelve Jesus sent on a mission, after giving them their instructions:»Go not,« He said, »among the Gentiles, and enter no Samaritan town;
B040C010V006	40	10	6	but, instead of that, go to the lost sheep of Israel's race.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you go, preach and say, `The Kingdom of the Heavens is close at hand.'
B040C010V008	40	10	8	Cure the sick, raise the dead to life, cleanse lepers, drive out demons: you have received without payment, give without payment.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	»Provide no gold, nor even silver nor copper to carry in your pockets;«
B040C010V010	40	10	10	no bag for your journey, nor change of linen, nor shoes, nor stick; for the labourer deserves his food.
B040C010V011	40	10	11	»Whatever town or village you enter, inquire for some good man; and make his house your home till you leave the place.«
B040C010V012	40	10	12	When you enter the house, salute it;
B040C010V013	40	10	13	and if the house deserves it, the peace you invoke shall come upon it. If not, your peace shall return to you.
B040C010V014	40	10	14	And whoever refuses to receive you or even to listen to your Message, as you leave that house or town, shake off the very dust from your feet.
B040C010V015	40	10	15	I solemnly tell you that it will be more endurable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah on the day of Judgement than for that town.
B040C010V016	40	10	16	»Remember it is I who am sending you out, as sheep into the midst of wolves; prove yourselves as sagacious as serpents, and as innocent as doves.«
B040C010V017	40	10	17	But beware of men; for they will deliver you up to appear before Sanhedrins, and will flog you in their synagogues;
B040C010V018	40	10	18	and you will even be put on trial before governors and kings for my sake, to bear witness to them and to the Gentiles.
B040C010V019	40	10	19	But when they have delivered you up, have no anxiety as to how you shall speak or what you shall say; for at that very time it shall be given you what to say;
B040C010V020	40	10	20	for it is not you who will speak: it will be the Spirit of your Father speaking through you.
B040C010V021	40	10	21	Brother will betray brother to death, and father, child; and children will rise against their own parents and will put them to death.
B040C010V022	40	10	22	And you will be objects of universal hatred because you are called by my name; but he who holds out to the End–he will be saved.
B040C010V023	40	10	23	Whenever they persecute you in one town, escape to the next; for I solemnly tell you that you will not have gone the round of all the towns of Israel before the Son of Man comes.
B040C010V024	40	10	24	»The learner is never superior to his teacher, and the servant is never superior to his master.«
B040C010V025	40	10	25	Enough for the learner to be on a level with his teacher, and for the servant to be on a level with his master. If they have called the master of the house Baal-zebul, how much more will they slander his servants?
B040C010V026	40	10	26	Fear them not, however; there is nothing veiled which will not be uncovered, nor secret which will not become known.
B040C010V027	40	10	27	What I tell you in the dark, speak in the light; and what is whispered into your ear, proclaim upon the roofs of the houses.
B040C010V028	40	10	28	»And do not fear those who kill the body, but cannot kill the soul; but rather fear him who is able to destroy both soul and body in Gehenna.«
B040C010V029	40	10	29	Do not two sparrows sell for a halfpenny? Yet not one of them will fall to the ground without your Father's leave.
B040C010V030	40	10	30	But as for you, the very hairs on your heads are all numbered.
B040C010V031	40	10	31	Away then with fear; you are more precious than a multitude of sparrows.
B040C010V032	40	10	32	»Every man who acknowledges me before men I also will acknowledge before my Father who is in Heaven.«
B040C010V033	40	10	33	But whoever disowns me before men I also will disown before my Father who is in Heaven.
B040C010V034	40	10	34	»Do not suppose that I came to bring peace to the earth: I did not come to bring peace but a sword.«
B040C010V035	40	10	35	For I came to set a man against his father, 
B040C010V036	40	10	36	
        
B040C010V037	40	10	37	Any one who loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me, and any one who loves son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me;
B040C010V038	40	10	38	and any one who does not take up his cross and follow where I lead is not worthy of me.
B040C010V039	40	10	39	To save your life is to lose it, and to lose your life for my sake is to save it.
B040C010V040	40	10	40	»Whoever receives you receives me, and whoever receives me receives Him who sent me.«
B040C010V041	40	10	41	Every one who receives a prophet, because he is a prophet, will receive a prophet's reward, and every one who receives a righteous man, because he is a righteous man, will receive a righteous man's reward.
B040C010V042	40	10	42	And whoever gives one of these little ones even a cup of cold water to drink because he is a disciple, I solemnly tell you that he will not lose his reward.«
B040C011V001	40	11	1	When Jesus had concluded His instructions to His twelve disciples, He left in order to teach and to proclaim His Message in the neighbouring towns.
B040C011V002	40	11	2	Now John had heard in prison about the Christ's doings, and he sent some of his disciples to inquire:
B040C011V003	40	11	3	»Are you the Coming One, or is it a different person that we are to expect?«
B040C011V004	40	11	4	»Go and report to John what you see and hear,« replied Jesus;«
B040C011V005	40	11	5	»blind eyes receive sight, and cripples walk; lepers are cleansed, and deaf ears hear; the dead are raised to life, and the poor have the Good News proclaimed to them;«
B040C011V006	40	11	6	and blessed is every one who does not stumble and fall because of my claims.«
B040C011V007	40	11	7	When the messengers had taken their leave, Jesus proceeded to say to the multitude concerning John, »What did you go out into the Desert to gaze at? A reed waving in the wind?
B040C011V008	40	11	8	But what did you go out to see? A man luxuriously dressed? Those who wear luxurious clothes are to be found in kings' palaces.
B040C011V009	40	11	9	But why did you go out? To see a prophet? Yes, I tell you, and far more than a prophet.
B040C011V010	40	11	10	This is he of whom it is written, 
B040C011V011	40	11	11	»I solemnly tell you that among all of woman born no greater has ever been raised up than John the Baptist; yet one who is of lower rank in the Kingdom of the Heavens is greater than he.«
B040C011V012	40	11	12	But from the time of John the Baptist till now, the Kingdom of the Heavens has been suffering violent assault, and the violent have been seizing it by force.
B040C011V013	40	11	13	For all the Prophets and the Law taught until John.
B040C011V014	40	11	14	And (if you are willing to receive it) he is the Elijah who was to come.
B040C011V015	40	11	15	Listen, every one who has ears!
B040C011V016	40	11	16	»But to what shall I compare the present generation? It is like children sitting in the open places, who call to their playmates.«
B040C011V017	40	11	17	»`We have played the flute to you,' they say, `and you have not danced: we have sung dirges, and you have not beaten your breasts.'«
B040C011V018	40	11	18	»For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, `He has a demon.'
B040C011V019	40	11	19	The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they exclaim, `See this man! –given to gluttony and tippling, and a friend of tax-gatherers and notorious sinners!' And yet Wisdom is vindicated by her actions.«
B040C011V020	40	11	20	Then began He to upbraid the towns where most of His mighty works had been done–because they had not repented.
B040C011V021	40	11	21	»Alas for thee, Chorazin!« He cried. »Alas for thee, Bethsaida! For had the mighty works been done in Tyre and Sidon which have been done in both of you, they would long ere now have repented, covered with sackcloth and ashes.
B040C011V022	40	11	22	Only I tell you that it will be more endurable for Tyre and Sidon on the day of Judgement than for you.
B040C011V023	40	11	23	And thou, Capernaum, shalt thou be exalted even to Heaven? Even to Hades shalt thou descend. For had the mighty works been done in Sodom which have been done in thee, it would have remained until now.
B040C011V024	40	11	24	Only I tell you all, that it will be more endurable for the land of Sodom on the day of Judgement than for thee.«
B040C011V025	40	11	25	About that time Jesus exclaimed, »I heartily praise Thee, Father, Lord of Heaven and of earth, that Thou hast hidden these things from sages and men of discernment, and hast unveiled them to babes.
B040C011V026	40	11	26	Yes, Father, for such has been Thy gracious will.
B040C011V027	40	11	27	»All things have been handed over to me by my Father, and no one fully knows the Son except the Father, nor does any one fully know the Father except the Son and all to whom the Son chooses to reveal Him.«
B040C011V028	40	11	28	»Come to me, all you toiling and burdened ones, and 
B040C011V029	40	11	29	Take my yoke upon you and learn from me; for I am gentle and lowly in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.
B040C011V030	40	11	30	For it is good to bear my yoke, and my burden is light.«
B040C012V001	40	12	1	About that time Jesus passed on the Sabbath through the wheatfields; and His disciples became hungry, and began to gather ears of wheat and eat them.
B040C012V002	40	12	2	But the Pharisees saw it and said to Him, »Look! your disciples are doing what the Law forbids them to do on the Sabbath.«
B040C012V003	40	12	3	»Have you never read,« He replied, »what David did when he and his men were hungry?
B040C012V004	40	12	4	how he entered the House of God and ate the Presented Loaves, which it was not lawful for him or his men to eat, nor for any except the priests?
B040C012V005	40	12	5	And have you not read in the Law how on the Sabbath the priests in the Temple break the Sabbath without incurring guilt?
B040C012V006	40	12	6	But I tell you that there is here that which is greater than the Temple.
B040C012V007	40	12	7	And if you knew what this means, 
B040C012V008	40	12	8	For the Son of Man is the Lord of the Sabbath.«
B040C012V009	40	12	9	Departing thence He went to their synagogue,
B040C012V010	40	12	10	where there was a man with a shrivelled arm. And they questioned Him, »Is it right to cure people on the Sabbath?« Their intention was to bring a charge against Him.
B040C012V011	40	12	11	»Which of you is there,« He replied, »who, if he has but a single sheep and it falls into a hole on the Sabbath, will not lay hold of it and lift it out?
B040C012V012	40	12	12	Is not a man, however, far superior to a sheep? Therefore it is right to do good on the Sabbath.«
B040C012V013	40	12	13	Then He said to the man, »Stretch out your arm.« And he stretched it out, and it was restored quite sound like the other.
B040C012V014	40	12	14	But the Pharisees after leaving the synagogue consulted together against Him, how they might destroy Him.
B040C012V015	40	12	15	Aware of this, Jesus departed elsewhere; and a great number of people followed Him, all of whom He cured.
B040C012V016	40	12	16	But He gave them strict injunctions not to blaze abroad His doings,
B040C012V017	40	12	17	that those words of the Prophet Isaiah might be fulfilled,
