B040C024V049	40	24	49	and should begin to beat his fellow servants, while he eats and drinks with drunkards;
B040C024V050	40	24	50	the master of that servant will arrive on a day when he is not expecting him and at an hour of which he has not been informed;
B040C024V051	40	24	51	he will treat him with the utmost severity and assign him a place among the hypocrites: there will be the weeping and the gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V001	40	25	1	»Then will the Kingdom of the Heavens be found to be like ten bridesmaids who took their torches and went out to meet the bridegroom.«
B040C025V002	40	25	2	Five of them were foolish and five were wise.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	For the foolish, when they took their torches, did not provide themselves with oil;
B040C025V004	40	25	4	but the wise, besides their torches, took oil in their flasks.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	The bridegroom was a long time in coming, so that meanwhile they all became drowsy and fell asleep.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	But at midnight there is a loud cry, »`The bridegroom! Go out and meet him!'
B040C025V007	40	25	7	»Then all those bridesmaids roused themselves and trimmed their torches.«
B040C025V008	40	25	8	»`Give us some of your oil,' said the foolish ones to the wise, `for our torches are going out.'«
B040C025V009	40	25	9	»`But perhaps,' replied the wise, `there will not be enough for all of us. Go to the shops rather, and buy some for yourselves.'«
B040C025V010	40	25	10	»So they went to buy. But meanwhile the bridegroom came; those bridesmaids who were ready went in with him to the wedding banquet; and the door was shut.«
B040C025V011	40	25	11	»Afterwards the other bridesmaids came and cried,« `Sir, Sir, open the door to us.'
B040C025V012	40	25	12	»`In solemn truth I tell you,' he replied, `I do not know you.'«
B040C025V013	40	25	13	»Keep awake therefore; for you know neither the day nor the hour.«
B040C025V014	40	25	14	»Why, it is like a man who, when going on his travels, called his bondservants and entrusted his property to their care.«
B040C025V015	40	25	15	To one he gave five talents, to another two, to another one–to each according to his individual capacity; and then started from home.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	Without delay the one who had received the five talents went and employed them in business, and gained five more.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	In the same way he who had the two gained two more.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	But the man who had received the one went and dug a hole and buried his master's money.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	»After a long lapse of time the master of those servants returned, and had a reckoning with them.«
B040C025V020	40	25	20	The one who had received the five talents came and brought five more, and said, »`Sir, it was five talents that you entrusted to me: see, I have gained five more.'
B040C025V021	40	25	21	»`You have done well, good and trustworthy servant,' replied his master; `you have been trustworthy in the management of a little, I will put you in charge of much: share your master's joy.'«
B040C025V022	40	25	22	»The second, who had received the two talents, came and said,« `Sir, it was two talents you entrusted to me: see, I have gained two more.'
B040C025V023	40	25	23	»`Good and trustworthy servant, you have done well,' his master replied; `you have been trustworthy in the management of a little, I will put you in charge of much: share your master's joy.'«
