B040C026V007	40	26	7	a woman came to Him with a jar of very costly, sweet-scented ointment, which she poured over His head as He reclined at table.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	»Why such waste?« indignantly exclaimed the disciples;
B040C026V009	40	26	9	»for this might have been sold for a considerable sum, and the money given to the poor.«
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But Jesus heard it, and said to them, »Why are you vexing her? For she has done a most gracious act towards me.
B040C026V011	40	26	11	The poor you always have with you, but me you have not always.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	In pouring this ointment over me, her object was to prepare me for burial.
B040C026V013	40	26	13	In solemn truth I tell you that wherever in the whole world this Good News shall be proclaimed, this deed of hers shall be spoken of in memory of her.«
