B041C005V003	41	5	3	This man lived among the tombs, nor could any one now secure him even with a chain;
B041C005V004	41	5	4	for many a time he had been left securely bound in fetters and chains, but afterwards the chains lay torn link from link, and the fetters in fragments, and there was no one strong enough to master him.
