B041C005V010	41	5	10	And he earnestly entreated Him not to send them away out of the country.
B041C005V011	41	5	11	Feeding there, on the mountain slope, was a great herd of swine.
B041C005V012	41	5	12	So they besought Jesus. »Send us to the swine,« they said, »so that we may enter into them.«
B041C005V013	41	5	13	He gave them leave; and the foul spirits came out and entered into the swine, and the herd –about 2,000 in number– rushed headlong down the cliff into the Lake and were drowned in the Lake.
