B041C005V043	41	5	43	but He gave strict injunctions that the matter should not be made known, and directed them to give her something to eat.
B041C006V001	41	6	1	Leaving that place He came into His own country, accompanied by His disciples.
B041C006V002	41	6	2	On the Sabbath He proceeded to teach in the synagogue; and many, as they heard Him, were astonished. »Where did he acquire all this?« they asked. »What is this wisdom that has been given to him? And what are these marvellous miracles which his hands perform?
B041C006V003	41	6	3	Is not this the carpenter, Mary's son, the brother of James and Joses, Jude and Simon? And do not his sisters live here among us?« So they turned angrily away.
B041C006V004	41	6	4	But Jesus said to them, »There is no Prophet without honour except in his own country, and among his own relatives, and in his own home.«
B041C006V005	41	6	5	And He could not do any miracle there, except that He laid His hands on a few who were out of health and cured them; and
B041C006V006	41	6	6	He wondered at their unbelief. So He went round the adjacent villages, teaching.
