B041C015V036	41	15	36	Then a man ran to fill a sponge with sour wine, and he put it on the end of a cane and placed it to His lips, saying at the same time, »Wait! let us see whether Elijah will come and take him down.«
B041C015V037	41	15	37	But Jesus uttered a loud cry and yielded up His spirit.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	And the curtain in the Sanctuary was torn in two, from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	And when the Centurion who stood in front of the cross saw that He was dead, he exclaimed, »This man was indeed God's Son.«
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were also a party of women looking on from a distance; among them being both Mary of Magdala and Mary the mother of James the Little and of Joses, and Salome–
B041C015V041	41	15	41	all of whom in the Galilaean days had habitually been with Him and cared for Him, as well as many other women who had come up to Jerusalem with Him.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	Towards sunset, as it was the Preparation –that is, the day preceding the Sabbath–
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathaea came, a highly respected member of the Council, who himself also was living in expectation of the Kingdom of God. He summoned up courage to go in to see Pilate and beg for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	But Pilate could hardly believe that He was already dead. He called, however, for the Centurion and inquired whether He had been long dead;
B041C015V045	41	15	45	and having ascertained the fact he granted the body to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	He, having bought a sheet of linen, took Him down, wrapped Him in the sheet and laid Him in a tomb hewn in the rock; after which he rolled a stone against the entrance to the tomb.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	Mary of Magdala and Mary the mother of Joses were looking on to see where He was put.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	When the Sabbath was over, Mary of Magdala, Mary the mother of James, and Salome, bought spices, in order to come and anoint His body.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	So, very soon after sunrise on the first day of the week, they came to the tomb;
B041C016V003	41	16	3	and they were saying to one another, `Who will roll away the stone for us from the entrance to the tomb?«
B041C016V004	41	16	4	But then, looking up, they saw that the stone was already rolled back: for it was of immense size.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	Upon entering the tomb, they saw a young man sitting at their right hand, clothed in a long white robe. They were astonished and terrified.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, »Do not be terrified. It is Jesus you are looking for–the Nazarene who has been crucified. He has come back to life: He is not here: this is the place where they laid Him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go and tell His disciples and Peter that He is going before you into Galilee: and that there you will see Him, as He told you.«
B041C016V008	41	16	8	So they came out, and fled from the tomb, for they were greatly agitated and surprised; and they said not a word to any one, for they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	[But He rose to life early on the first day of the week, and appeared first to Mary of Magdala from whom He had expelled seven demons.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	She went and brought the tidings to those who had been with Him, as they were mourning and weeping.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	But they, when they were told that He was alive and that she had seen Him, could not believe it.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	Afterwards He showed Himself in another form to two of them as they were walking, on their way into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	These, again, went and told the news to the rest; but not even them did they believe.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	Later still He showed Himself to the Eleven themselves whilst they were at table, and He upbraided them with their unbelief and obstinacy in not having believed those who had seen Him alive.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	Then He said to them, »Go the whole world over, and proclaim the Good News to all mankind.
B041C016V016	41	16	16	He who believes and is baptized shall be saved, but he who disbelieves will be condemned.
B041C016V017	41	16	17	And signs shall attend those who believe, even such as these. By making use of my name they shall expel demons. They shall speak new languages.
B041C016V018	41	16	18	They shall take up venomous snakes, and if they drink any deadly poison it shall do them no harm whatever. They shall lay their hands on the sick, and the sick shall recover.«
B041C016V019	41	16	19	So the Lord Jesus after having thus spoken to them was taken up into Heaven, and sat down at the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	But they went out and made proclamation everywhere, the Lord working with them and confirming their Message by the signs which accompanied it.]
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Seeing that many have attempted to draw up a narrative of the facts which are received with full assurance among us
B042C001V002	42	1	2	on the authority of those who were from the beginning eye-witnesses and were devoted to the service of the divine Message,
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it has seemed right to me also, after careful investigation of the facts from their commencement, to write for you, most noble Theophilus, a connected account,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	that you may fully know the truth of the things which you have been taught by word of mouth.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	There was in the time of Herod, the king of Judaea, a priest of the name of Zechariah, belonging to the class of Abijah. He had a wife who was a descendant of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	They were both of them upright before God, blamelessly obeying all the Lord's precepts and ordinances.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	But they had no child, because Elizabeth was barren; and both of them were far advanced in life.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	Now while he was doing priestly duty before God in the prescribed course of his class,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	it fell to his lot –according to the custom of the priesthood– to go into the Sanctuary of the Lord and burn the incense;
B042C001V010	42	1	10	and the whole multitude of the people were outside praying, at the hour of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	Then there appeared to him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense;
B042C001V012	42	1	12	and Zechariah on seeing him was agitated and terrified.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, »Do not be afraid, Zechariah, for your petition has been heard: and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and you are to call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	Gladness and exultant joy shall be yours, and many will rejoice over his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he will be great in the sight of the Lord; no wine or fermented drink shall he ever drink; but he will be filled with the Holy Spirit from the very hour of his birth.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	Many of the descendants of Israel will he turn to the Lord their God;
B042C001V017	42	1	17	and he will be His forerunner in the spirit and power of Elijah, to turn fathers' hearts to the children, and cause the rebellious to walk in the wisdom of the upright, to make a people perfectly ready for the lord.«
B042C001V018	42	1	18	»By what proof,« asked Zechariah, »shall I know this? For I am an old man, and my wife is far advanced in years.«
B042C001V019	42	1	19	»I am Gabriel, who stand in the presence of God,« answered the angel, »and I have been sent to talk with you and tell you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	And now you will be dumb and unable to speak until the day when this has taken place; because you did not believe my words–words which will be fulfilled at their appointed time.«
B042C001V021	42	1	21	Meanwhile the people were waiting for Zechariah, and were surprised that he stayed so long in the Sanctuary.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	When, however, he came out, he was unable to speak to them; and they knew that he must have seen a vision in the Sanctuary; but he kept making signs to them and continued dumb.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	When his days of service were at an end, he went to his home;
B042C001V024	42	1	24	and in course of time his wife Elizabeth conceived, and kept herself secluded five months.
B042C001V025	42	1	25	»Thus has the Lord dealt with me,« she said, »now that He has graciously taken away my reproach among men.«
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Now in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a town in Galilee called Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a maiden betrothed to a man of the name of Joseph, a descendant of David. The maiden's name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	So Gabriel went into the house and said to her, »Joy be to you, favoured one! the Lord is with you.«
B042C001V029	42	1	29	She was greatly agitated at his words, and wondered what such a greeting meant.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	But the angel said, »Do not be frightened, Mary, for you have found favour with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	You will conceive in your womb and bear a son; and you are to call His name JESUS.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He will be great and He will be called `Son of the Most High.' And the Lord God will give Him the throne of His forefather David;
B042C001V033	42	1	33	and He will be King over the House of Jacob for the Ages, and of His Kingdom there will be no end.«
B042C001V034	42	1	34	»How can this be,« Mary replied, »seeing that I have no husband?«
B042C001V035	42	1	35	The angel answered, »The Holy Spirit will come upon you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you; and for this reason your holy offspring will be called `the Son of God.'
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And see, your relative Elizabeth–she also has conceived a son in her old age; and this is the sixth month with her who was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For no promise from God will be impossible of fulfilment.«
B042C001V038	42	1	38	»I am the Lord's maidservant,« Mary replied; »may it be with me in accordance with your words!« And then the angel left her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	Not long after this, Mary rose up and went in haste into the hill country to a town in Judah.
B042C001V040	42	1	40	Here she came to the house of Zechariah and greeted Elizabeth;
B042C001V041	42	1	41	and as soon as Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting, the babe leapt within her. And Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit,
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and uttered a loud cry of joy. »Blest among women are you,« she said, »and the offspring of your body is blest!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	But why is this honour done me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, the moment your greeting reached my ears, the babe within me leapt for joy.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And blessed is she who has believed, for the word spoken to her from the Lord shall be fulfilled.«
B042C001V046	42	1	46	Then Mary said: »My soul extols the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	And my spirit triumphs in God my Saviour;
B042C001V048	42	1	48	Because He has not turned from His maidservant in her lowly position; For from this time forward all generations will account me happy,
B042C001V049	42	1	49	Because the mighty One has done great things for me –Holy is His name!–
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And His compassion is, generation after generation, Upon those who fear Him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He has manifested His supreme strength. He has scattered those who were haughty in the thoughts of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He has cast monarchs down from their thrones, And exalted men of low estate.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	The hungry He has satisfied with choice gifts, But the rich He has sent empty-handed away.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	His servant Israel He has helped, Remembering His compassion–
B042C001V055	42	1	55	In fulfillment of His promises to our forefathers–For Abraham and his posterity for ever.«
B042C001V056	42	1	56	So Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months, and then returned home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now when Elizabeth's full time was come, she gave birth to a son;
B042C001V058	42	1	58	and her neighbours and relatives heard how the Lord had had great compassion on her; and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and were going to call him Zechariah, after his father.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	His mother, however, said, »No, he is to be called John.«
B042C001V061	42	1	61	»There is not one of your family,« they said, »who has that name.«
B042C001V062	42	1	62	They asked his father by signs what he wished him to be called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	So he asked for a writing-tablet, and wrote, »His name is John.« And they all wondered.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	Instantly his mouth and his tongue were set free, and he began to speak and bless God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And all who lived round about them were filled with awe, and throughout the hill country of Judaea reports of all these things were spread abroad.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	All who heard the story treasured it in their memories. »What then will this child be?« they said. For the lord's hand was indeed with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And Zechariah his father was filled with the Holy Spirit, and spoke in a rapture of praise.
B042C001V068	42	1	68	»Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,« he said, »Because He has not forgotten His people but has effected redemption for them,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	And has raised up a mighty Deliverer for us In the house of David His servant–
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As He has spoken from all time by the lips of His holy Prophets–
B042C001V071	42	1	71	To deliver us from our foes and from the power of all who hate us.
B042C001V072	42	1	72	He dealt pitifully with our forefathers, And remembered His holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	The oath which He swore to Abraham our forefather,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	To grant us to be rescued from the power of our foes And so render worship to Him free from fear,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	In piety and uprightness before Him all our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you moreover, O child, shall be called Prophet of the Most High; For you shall go on in front before the Lord to prepare the way for Him,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	To give to His People a knowledge of salvation In the forgiveness of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Through the tender compassion of our God, Through which the daybreak from on high will come to us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	Dawning on those who now dwell in the darkness and shadow of death–To direct our feet into the path of peace.«
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child grew and became strong in character, and lived in the Desert till the time came for him to appear publicly to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	Just at this time an edict was issued by Caesar Augustus for the registration of the whole Empire.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	It was the first registration made during the governorship of Quirinius in Syria;
B042C002V003	42	2	3	and all went to be registered–every one to the town to which he belonged.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	So Joseph went up from Galilee, from the town of Nazareth, to Judaea, to David's town of Bethlehem, because he was of the house and lineage of David,
B042C002V005	42	2	5	to have himself registered together with Mary, who was betrothed to him and was with child.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	But while they were there, her full time came,
B042C002V007	42	2	7	and she gave birth to her first-born son, and wrapped Him round, and laid Him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	Now there were shepherds in the same part of the country, keeping watch over their sheep by night in the open fields,
B042C002V009	42	2	9	when suddenly an angel of the Lord stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone round them; and they were filled with terror.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	But the angel said to them, »Put away all fear; for I am bringing you good news of great joy–joy for all the People.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	For a Saviour who is the Anointed Lord is born to you to-day, in the town of David.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this is the token for you: you will find a babe wrapped in swaddling clothes and lying in a manger.«
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And immediately there was with the angel a multitude of the army of Heaven praising God and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	»Glory be to God in the highest Heavens, And on earth peace among men who please Him!«
B042C002V015	42	2	15	Then, as soon as the angels had left them and returned to Heaven, the shepherds said to one another, »Let us now go over as far as Bethlehem and see this that has happened, which the Lord has made known to us.«
B042C002V016	42	2	16	So they made haste and came and found Mary and Joseph, with the babe lying in the manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	And when they saw the child, they told what had been said to them about Him;
B042C002V018	42	2	18	and all who listened were astonished at what the shepherds told them.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary treasured up all these things, often dwelling on them in her mind.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all that they had heard and seen in accordance with the announcement made to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	When eight days had passed and the time for circumcising Him had come, He was called JESUS, the name given Him by the angel before His conception in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when the days for their purification appointed by the Law of Moses had passed, they took Him up to Jerusalem to present Him to the Lord–
B042C002V023	42	2	23	as it is written in the Law of the Lord: 
B042C002V024	42	2	24	During the passage He fell asleep, and there came down a squall of wind on the Lake, so that the boat began to fill and they were in deadly peril.
B042C002V025	42	2	25	And they also offered a sacrifice as commanded in the Law of the Lord, 
B042C002V026	42	2	26	Now there was a man in Jerusalem of the name of Symeon, an upright and God-fearing man, who was waiting for the consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	To him it had been revealed by the Holy Spirit that he should not see death until he had seen the Lord's Anointed One.
B042C002V028	42	2	28	Led by the Spirit he came to the Temple; and when the parents brought in the child Jesus to do with regard to Him according to the custom of the Law,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	he took Him up in his arms and blessed God and said,
B042C002V030	42	2	30	»Now, O Sovereign Lord, Thou dost send Thy servant away in peace, in fulfilment of Thy word,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	Because mine eyes have seen Thy salvation,
B042C002V032	42	2	32	Which Thou hast made ready in the sight of all nations–
B042C002V033	42	2	33	A light to shine upon the Gentiles, And the glory of Thy people Israel.«
B042C002V034	42	2	34	And while the child's father and mother were wondering at the words of Symeon concerning Him,
B042C002V035	42	2	35	Symeon blessed them and said to Mary the mother, »This child is appointed for the falling and the uprising of many in Israel and for a token to be spoken against;
B042C002V036	42	2	36	and a sword will pierce through your own soul also; that the reasonings in many hearts may be revealed.«
B042C002V037	42	2	37	There was also Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, belonging to the tribe of Asher. She was of a very great age, having had after her maidenhood seven years of married life,
B042C002V038	42	2	38	and then being a widow of eighty-four years. She was never absent from the Temple, but worshipped, by day and by night, with fasting and prayer.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	And coming up just at that moment, she gave thanks to God, and spoke about the child to all who were expecting the deliverance of Jerusalem.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	Then, as soon as they had accomplished all that the Law required, they returned to Galilee to their own town of Nazareth.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	And the child grew and became strong and full of wisdom, and the favour of God rested upon Him.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	Now His parents used to go up year by year to Jerusalem at the Feast of the Passover.
B042C002V043	42	2	43	And when He was twelve years old they went up as was customary at the time of the Feast, and,
B042C002V044	42	2	44	after staying the full number of days, when they started back home the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem. His parents did not discover this,
B042C002V045	42	2	45	but supposing Him to be in the travelling company, they proceeded a day's journey. Then they searched up and down for Him among their relatives and acquaintances;
B042C002V046	42	2	46	but being unable to find Him they returned to Jerusalem, making anxious inquiry for Him.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	On the third day they found Him in the Temple sitting among the Rabbis, both listening to them and asking them questions,
B042C002V048	42	2	48	while all who heard Him were astonished at His intelligence and at the answers He gave.
B042C002V049	42	2	49	When they saw Him, they were smitten with amazement, and His mother said to Him, »My child, why have you behaved thus to us? Your father and I have been searching for you in anguish.«
B042C002V050	42	2	50	»Why is it that you have been searching for me?« He replied; »did you not know that it is my duty to be engaged upon my Father's business?«
B042C002V051	42	2	51	But they did not understand the significance of these words.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	Then He went down with them and came to Nazareth, and was always obedient to them; but His mother carefully treasured up all these incidents in her memory.
B042C002V053	42	2	53	And as Jesus grew older He gained in both wisdom and stature, and in favour with God and man.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being Governor of Judaea, Herod Tetrarch of Galilee, his brother Philip Tetrarch of Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias Tetrarch of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	during the High-priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, a message from God came to John, the son of Zechariah, in the Desert.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	John went into all the district about the Jordan proclaiming a baptism of the penitent for the forgiveness of sins;
B042C003V004	42	3	4	as it is written in the book of the prophet Isaiah, 
B042C003V005	42	3	5	
        
B042C003V006	42	3	6	
        
B042C003V007	42	3	7	Accordingly John used to say to the crowds who came out to be baptized by him, `O vipers' brood, who has warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Live lives which shall prove your change of heart; and do not begin to say to yourselves, `We have Abraham as our forefather,' for I tell you that God can raise up descendants for Abraham from these stones.
B042C003V009	42	3	9	And even now the axe is lying at the root of the trees, so that every tree which fails to yield good fruit will quickly be hewn down and thrown into the fire.«
B042C003V010	42	3	10	The crowds repeatedly asked him, »What then are we to do?«
B042C003V011	42	3	11	»Let the man who has two coats,« he answered, »give one to the man who has none; and let the man who has food share it with others.«
B042C003V012	42	3	12	There came also a party of tax-gatherers to be baptized, and they asked him, »Rabbi, what are we to do?«
B042C003V013	42	3	13	»Do not exact more than the legal amount,« he replied.
B042C003V014	42	3	14	The soldiers also once and again inquired of him, »And we, what are we to do?« His answer was, »Neither intimidate any one nor lay false charges; and be content with your pay.«
B042C003V015	42	3	15	And while the people were in suspense and all were debating in their minds whether John might possibly be the Anointed One,
B042C003V016	42	3	16	he answered the question by saying to them all, »As for me, I am baptizing you with water, but One mightier than I is coming, whose very sandal-strap I am not worthy to unfasten: He will baptize you in the Holy Spirit and with fire.
B042C003V017	42	3	17	His winnowing-shovel is in His hand to clear out His threshing-floor, and to gather the wheat into His storehouse; but the chaff He will burn up in fire unquenchable.«
B042C003V018	42	3	18	With many exhortations besides these he declared the Good News to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	But Herod the Tetrarch, being repeatedly rebuked by him about Herodias his brother's wife, and about all the wicked deeds that he had done,
B042C003V020	42	3	20	now added this to crown all the rest, that he threw John into prison.
B042C003V021	42	3	21	Now when all the people had been baptized, and Jesus also had been baptized and was praying, the sky opened,
B042C003V022	42	3	22	and the Holy Spirit came down in bodily shape, like a dove, upon Him, and a voice came from Heaven, which said, »Thou art My Son, dearly loved: in Thee is My delight.«
B042C003V023	42	3	23	And He –Jesus– when He began His ministry, was about thirty years old. He was the son (it was supposed) of Joseph, son of Heli,
B042C003V024	42	3	24	son of Matthat, son of Levi, son of Melchi, son of Jannai, son of Joseph,
B042C003V025	42	3	25	son of Mattathias, son of Amos, son of Nahum, son of Esli, son of Naggai,
B042C003V026	42	3	26	son of Mahath, son of Mattathias, son of Semein, son of Josech, son of Joda,
B042C003V027	42	3	27	son of Johanan, son of Resa, son of Zerubbabel, son of Shealtiel, son of Neri,
B042C003V028	42	3	28	son of Melchi, son of Addi, son of Cosam, son of Elmadam, son of Er,
B042C003V029	42	3	29	son of Joshua, son of Eliezar, son of Jorim, son of Maththat, son of Levi,
B042C003V030	42	3	30	son of Symeon, son of Judah, son of Joseph, son of Jonam, son of Eliakim, son of
B042C003V031	42	3	31	Melea, son of Menna, son of Mattatha, son of Nathan, son of David,
B042C003V032	42	3	32	son of Jesse, son of Obed, son of Boaz, son of Salmon, son of Nahshon,
B042C003V033	42	3	33	son of Amminadab, son of Admin, son of Arni, son of Hezron, son of Perez, son of Judah,
B042C003V034	42	3	34	son of Jacob, son of Isaac, son of Abraham, son of Terah, son of Nahor,
