B042C004V018	42	4	18	
        
B042C004V019	42	4	19	
        
B042C004V020	42	4	20	And rolling up the book, He returned it to the attendant, and sat down–to speak. And the eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on Him.
B042C004V021	42	4	21	Then He proceeded to say to them, »To-day is this Scripture fulfilled in your hearing.«
B042C004V022	42	4	22	And they all spoke well of Him, wondering at the sweet words of kindness which fell from His lips, while they asked one another, »Is not this Joseph's son?«
B042C004V023	42	4	23	»Doubtless,« said He, »you will quote to me the proverb, `Physician, cure yourself: all that we hear that you have done at Capernaum, do here also in your native place.'«
B042C004V024	42	4	24	»I tell you in solemn truth,« He added, »that no Prophet is welcomed among his own people.
B042C004V025	42	4	25	But I tell you in truth that there was many a widow in Israel in the time of Elijah, when there was no rain for three years and six months and there came a severe famine over all the land;
B042C004V026	42	4	26	and yet to not one of them was Elijah sent: he was only sent to a widow at Zarephath in the Sidonian country.
B042C004V027	42	4	27	And there was also many a leper in Israel in the time of the Prophet Elisha, and yet not one of them was cleansed, but Naaman the Syrian was.«
B042C004V028	42	4	28	Then all in the synagogue, while listening to these words, were filled with fury.
B042C004V029	42	4	29	They rose, hurried Him outside the town, and brought Him to the brow of the hill on which their town was built, to throw Him down the cliff;
B042C004V030	42	4	30	but He passed through the midst of them and went His way.
B042C004V031	42	4	31	So He came down to Capernaum, a town in Galilee, where He frequently taught the people on the Sabbath days.
B042C004V032	42	4	32	And they were greatly impressed by His teaching, because He spoke with the language of authority.
B042C004V033	42	4	33	But in the synagogue there was a man possessed by the spirit of a foul demon. In a loud voice he cried out,
B042C004V034	42	4	34	»Ha! Jesus the Nazarene, what have you to do with us? I know who you are–God's Holy One!«
B042C004V035	42	4	35	But Jesus rebuked the demon. »Silence!« He exclaimed; »come out of him.« Upon this, the demon hurled the man into the midst of them, and came out of him without doing him any harm.
B042C004V036	42	4	36	All were astonished and awe-struck; and they asked one another, »What sort of language is this? For with authority and real power He gives orders to the foul spirits and they come out.«
