B042C004V041	42	4	41	Demons also came out of many, loudly calling out, »You are the Son of God.« But He rebuked them and forbad them to speak, because they knew Him to be the Christ.
B042C004V042	42	4	42	Next morning, at daybreak, He left the town and went away to a solitary place; but the people flocked out to find Him, and, coming to the place where He was, they endeavoured to detain Him that He might not leave them.
B042C004V043	42	4	43	But He said to them, »I have to tell the Good News of the Kingdom of God to the other towns also, because for this purpose I was sent.«
B042C004V044	42	4	44	And for some time He preached in the synagogues in Galilee.
B042C005V001	42	5	1	On one occasion the crowd was pressing on Him and listening to God's Message, while He was standing by the Lake of Gennesaret.
B042C005V002	42	5	2	He, however, saw two fishing-boats drawn up on the beach (for the men had gone away from them and were washing the nets),
B042C005V003	42	5	3	and going on board one of them, which was Simon's He asked him to push out a little from land. Then He sat down and taught the crowd of people from the boat.
