B042C005V039	42	5	39	Nor does any one after drinking old wine wish for new; for he says, `The old is better.'«
B042C006V001	42	6	1	Now on the second-first Sabbath while He was passing through the wheatfields, His disciples were plucking the ears and rubbing them with their hands to eat the grain.
B042C006V002	42	6	2	And some of the Pharisees asked, »Why are you doing what the Law forbids on the Sabbath?«
B042C006V003	42	6	3	»Have you never read so much as this,« answered Jesus– »what David did when he and his followers were hungry;
B042C006V004	42	6	4	how he entered the house of God and took and ate the Presented Loaves and gave some to his followers–loaves which none but the Priests are allowed to eat?«
B042C006V005	42	6	5	»The Son of Man,« He added, »is Lord of the Sabbath also.«
B042C006V006	42	6	6	On another Sabbath He had gone to the synagogue and was teaching there; and in the congregation was a man whose right arm was withered.
