B042C007V016	42	7	16	All were awe-struck, and they gave glory to God–some saying, »A Prophet, a great Prophet, has risen up among us.« Others said, »God has not forgotten His People.«
B042C007V017	42	7	17	And the report of what Jesus had done spread through the whole of Judaea and in all the surrounding districts.
B042C007V018	42	7	18	John's disciples brought him an account of all these things;
B042C007V019	42	7	19	so John called two of his disciples and sent them to the Lord. »Are you the Coming One?« he asked, »or is there another that we are to expect?«
B042C007V020	42	7	20	The men came to Jesus and said, »John the Baptist has sent us to you with this question: `Are you the Coming One, or is there another that we are to expect?'«
B042C007V021	42	7	21	He immediately cured many of diseases, severe pain, and evil spirits, and to many who were blind He gave the gift of sight.
B042C007V022	42	7	22	Then He answered the messengers, »Go and report to John what you have seen and heard. Blind men receive sight, the lame walk, lepers are purified, deaf persons hear, the dead are raised to life, the poor have the Good News proclaimed to them.
B042C007V023	42	7	23	And blessed is every one who does not stumble and fall because of my claims.«
B042C007V024	42	7	24	When John's messengers were gone, He proceeded to say to the multitude concerning John, »What did you go out into the Desert to gaze at? A reed waving in the wind?
B042C007V025	42	7	25	But what did you go out to see? A man wearing luxurious clothes? People who are gorgeously dressed and live in luxury are found in palaces.
B042C007V026	42	7	26	But what did you go out to see? A Prophet? Aye, I tell you, and far more than a Prophet.
B042C007V027	42	7	27	John is the man about whom it is written, 
B042C007V028	42	7	28	»I tell you that among all of women born there is not one greater than John. Yet one who is of lower rank in the Kingdom of God is greater than he.«
B042C007V029	42	7	29	And all the people, including the tax-gatherers, when they listened to him upheld the righteousness of God, by being baptized with John's baptism.
B042C007V030	42	7	30	But the Pharisees and expounders of the Law have frustrated God's purpose as to their own lives, by refusing to be baptized.
B042C007V031	42	7	31	»To what then shall I compare the men of the present generation, and what do they resemble?«
