B042C007V035	42	7	35	But wisdom is justified by all who are truly wise.«
B042C007V036	42	7	36	Now one of the Pharisees repeatedly invited Him to a meal at his house; so He entered the house and reclined at the table.
B042C007V037	42	7	37	And there was a woman in the town who was a notorious sinner. Having learnt that Jesus was at table in the Pharisee's house she brought a flask of perfume,
B042C007V038	42	7	38	and, standing behind close to His feet, weeping, began to wet His feet with her tears; and with her hair she wiped the tears away again, while she lovingly kissed His feet and poured the perfume over them.
B042C007V039	42	7	39	Noticing this, the Pharisee, His host, said to himself, »This man, if he were really a Prophet, would know who and what sort of person this woman is who is touching him–and would know that she is an immoral woman.«
