B042C011V021	42	11	21	»Whenever a strong man, fully armed and equipped, is guarding his own castle, he enjoys peaceful possession of his property;«
B042C011V022	42	11	22	but as soon as another stronger than he attacks him and overcomes him, he takes away that complete armour of his in which he trusted, and distributes the plunder he has collected.
