B042C011V034	42	11	34	The lamp of the body is the eye. When your eyesight is good, your whole body also is lighted up; but when it is defective, your body is darkened.
B042C011V035	42	11	35	Consider therefore whether the light that is in you is anything but mere darkness.
B042C011V036	42	11	36	If, however, your whole body is penetrated with light, and has no part dark, it will be so lighted, all of it, as when the lamp with its bright shining gives you light.«
B042C011V037	42	11	37	When He had thus spoken, a Pharisee invited Him to breakfast at his house; so He entered and took His place at table.
B042C011V038	42	11	38	Now the Pharisee saw to his surprise that He did not wash His hands before breakfasting.
B042C011V039	42	11	39	The Master however said to him, »Here we see how you Pharisees clean the outside of the cup or plate, while your secret hearts are full of greed and selfishness.
