B042C012V019	42	12	19	and I will say to my life, »`Life, you have ample possessions laid up for many years to come: take your ease, eat, drink, enjoy yourself.'
B042C012V020	42	12	20	»But God said to him,« `Foolish man, this night your life is demanded from you; and these preparations–for whom shall they be?'
B042C012V021	42	12	21	»So is it with him who amasses treasure for himself, but has no riches in God.«
