B058C009V019	58	9	19	For when Moses had proclaimed to all the people every commandment contained in the Law, he took the blood of the calves and of the goats and with them water, scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book itself and all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	saying, 
B058C009V021	58	9	21	And in the same way he also sprinkled blood upon the Tent of worship and upon all the vessels used in the ministry.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	Indeed we may almost say that in obedience to the Law everything is sprinkled with blood, and that apart from the outpouring of blood there is no remission of sins.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	It was needful therefore that the copies of the things in Heaven should be cleansed in this way, but that the heavenly things themselves should be cleansed with more costly sacrifices.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For not into a Holy place built by men's hands –a mere copy of the reality– did Christ enter, but He entered Heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God on our behalf.
B058C009V025	58	9	25	Nor did He enter for the purpose of many times offering Himself in sacrifice, just as the High Priest enters the Holy place, year after year, taking with him blood not his own.
B058C009V026	58	9	26	In that case Christ would have needed to suffer many times, from the creation of the world onwards; but as a matter of fact He has appeared once for all, at the Close of the Ages, in order to do away with sin by the sacrifice of Himself.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And since it is reserved for all mankind once to die, and afterwards to be judged;
B058C009V028	58	9	28	so the Christ also, having been once offered in sacrifice in order that He might bear the sins of many, will appear a second time, separated from sin, to those who are eagerly expecting Him, to make their salvation complete.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For, since the Law exhibits only an outline of the blessings to come and not a perfect representation of the things themselves, the priests can never, by repeating the same sacrifices which they continually offer year after year, give complete freedom from sin to those who draw near.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	For then would not the sacrifices have ceased to be offered, because the consciences of the worshippers –who in that case would now have been cleansed once for all– would no longer be burdened with sins?
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But in those sacrifices sins are recalled to memory year after year.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	That is why, when He comes into the world, He says, 
B058C010V006	58	10	6	
        
B058C010V007	58	10	7	
        
B058C010V008	58	10	8	After saying the words I have just quoted, 
B058C010V009	58	10	9	He then adds, 
B058C010V010	58	10	10	It is through that divine will that we have been set free from sin, through the offering of Jesus Christ as our sacrifice once for all.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	And while every priest stands ministering, day after day, and constantly offering the same sacrifices –though such can never rid us of our sins–
B058C010V012	58	10	12	this Priest, on the contrary, after offering for sins a single sacrifice of perpetual efficacy, took His seat at God's right hand,
B058C010V013	58	10	13	waiting from that time onward until His enemies be put as a footstool under His feet.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by a single offering He has for ever completed the blessing for those whom He is setting free from sin.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	And the Holy Spirit also gives us His testimony; for when He had said,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	
        
B058C010V017	58	10	17	He adds, 
B058C010V018	58	10	18	But where these have been forgiven no further offering for sin is required.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Since then, brethren, we have free access to the Holy place through the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	by the new and ever-living way which He opened up for us through the rending of the veil –that is to say, of His earthly nature–
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and since we have a great Priest who has authority over the house of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	let us draw near with sincerity and unfaltering faith, having had our hearts sprinkled, once for all, from consciences oppressed with sin, and our bodies bathed in pure water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us hold firmly to an unflinching avowal of our hope, for He is faithful who gave us the promises.
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us bestow thought on one another with a view to arousing one another to brotherly love and right conduct;
B058C010V025	58	10	25	not neglecting –as some habitually do– to meet together, but encouraging one another, and doing this all the more since you can see the day of Christ approaching.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we wilfully persist in sin after having received the full knowledge of the truth, there no longer remains in reserve any other sacrifice for sins.
B058C010V027	58	10	27	There remains nothing but a certain awful expectation of judgement, and the fury of a fire which before long will devour the enemies of the truth.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	Any one who bids defiance to the Law of Moses is put to death without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses.
B058C010V029	58	10	29	How much severer punishment, think you, will he be held to deserve who has trampled under foot the Son of God, has not regarded as holy that Covenant-blood with which he was set free from sin, and has insulted the Spirit from whom comes grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know who it is that has said, 
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is an awful thing to fall into the hands of the ever-living God.
B058C010V032	58	10	32	But continually recall to mind the days now past, when on being first enlightened you went through a great conflict and many sufferings.
B058C010V033	58	10	33	This was partly through allowing yourselves to be made a public spectacle amid reproaches and persecutions, and partly through coming forward to share the sufferings of those who were thus treated.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you not only showed sympathy with those who were imprisoned, but you even submitted with joy when your property was taken from you, being well aware that you have in your own selves a more valuable possession and one which will remain.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Therefore do not cast from you your confident hope, for it will receive a vast reward.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	For you stand in need of patient endurance, so that, as the result of having done the will of God, you may receive the promised blessing.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	For there is still but a short time and then 
B058C010V038	58	10	38	
        
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not people who shrink back and perish, but are among those who believe and gain possession of their souls.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is a well-grounded assurance of that for which we hope, and a conviction of the reality of things which we do not see.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by it the saints of old won God's approval.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	Through faith we understand that the worlds came into being, and still exist, at the command of God, so that what is seen does not owe its existence to that which is visible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	Through faith Abel offered to God a more acceptable sacrifice than Cain did, and through this faith he obtained testimony that he was righteous, God giving the testimony by accepting his gifts; and through it, though he is dead, he still speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	Through faith Enoch was taken from the earth so that he did not see death, and he could not be found, because God had taken him; for before he was taken we have evidence that he truly pleased God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But where there is no faith it is impossible truly to please Him; for the man who draws near to God must believe that there is a God and that He proves Himself a rewarder of those who earnestly try to find Him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	Through faith Noah, being divinely taught about things as yet unseen, reverently gave heed and built an ark for the safety of his family, and by this act he condemned the world, and became an heir of the righteousness which depends on faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	Through faith Abraham, upon being called to leave home and go into a land which he was soon to receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing where he was going to.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	Through faith he came and made his home for a time in a land which had been promised to him, as if in a foreign country, living in tents together with Isaac and Jacob, sharers with him in the same promise;
B058C011V010	58	11	10	for he continually looked forward to the city which has the foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	Through faith even Sarah herself received strength to become a mother –although she was past the time of life for this– because she judged Him faithful who had given the promise.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	And thus there sprang from one man, and him practically dead, a nation like the stars of the sky in number, and like the sands on the sea shore which cannot be counted.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	All these died in the possession of faith. They had not received the promised blessings, but had seen them from a distance and had greeted them, and had acknowledged themselves to be foreigners and strangers here on earth;
B058C011V014	58	11	14	for men who acknowledge this make it manifest that they are seeking elsewhere a country of their own.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And if they had cherished the remembrance of the country they had left, they would have found an opportunity to return;
B058C011V016	58	11	16	but, as it is, we see them eager for a better land, that is to say, a heavenly one. For this reason God is not ashamed to be called their God, for He has now prepared a city for them.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	Through faith Abraham, as soon as God put him to the test, offered up Isaac. Yes, he who had joyfully welcomed the promises was on the point of sacrificing his only son
B058C011V018	58	11	18	with regard to whom he had been told, 
B058C011V019	58	11	19	For he reckoned that God is even able to raise a man up from among the dead, and, figuratively speaking, it was from among the dead that he received Isaac again.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	Through faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau, even in connexion with things soon to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	Through faith Jacob, when dying, blessed each of Joseph's sons, and, leaning on the top of his staff, worshipped God.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	Through faith Joseph, when he was near his end, made mention of the departure of the descendants of Israel, and gave orders about his own body.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	Through faith the child Moses was hid for three months by his parents, because they saw his rare beauty; and the king's edict had no terror for them.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	Through faith Moses, when he grew to manhood, refused to be known as Pharaoh's daughter's son,
B058C011V025	58	11	25	having determined to endure ill-treatment along with the people of God rather than enjoy the short-lived pleasures of sin;
B058C011V026	58	11	26	because he deemed the reproaches which he might meet with in the service of the Christ to be greater riches than all the treasures of Egypt; for he fixed his gaze on the coming reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	Through faith he left Egypt, not being frightened by the king's anger; for he held on his course as seeing the unseen One.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	Through faith he instituted the Passover, and the sprinkling with blood so that the destroyer of the firstborn might not touch the Israelites.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	Through faith they passed through the Red Sea as though they were passing over dry land, but the Egyptians, when they tried to do the same, were swallowed up.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	Through faith the walls of Jericho fell to the ground after being surrounded for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	Through faith the notorious sinner Rahab did not perish along with the disobedient, for she had welcomed the spies and had sheltered them.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And why need I say more? For time will fail me if I tell the story of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, and of David and Samuel and the Prophets;
B058C011V033	58	11	33	men who, as the result of faith, conquered whole kingdoms, brought about true justice, obtained promises from God, stopped lions' mouths,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	deprived fire of its power, escaped being killed by the sword, out of weakness were made strong, became mighty in war, put to flight foreign armies.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received back their dear ones alive from the dead; and others were put to death with torture, refusing the deliverance offered to them–that they might secure a better resurrection.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	Others again were tested by cruel mockery and by scourging; yes, and by chains and imprisonment.
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, they were sawn asunder, they were tried by temptation, they were killed with the sword. They went from place to place in sheepskins or goatskins, enduring want, oppression and cruelty.
B058C011V038	58	11	38	(They were men of whom the world was not worthy.) They wandered across deserts and mountains, or hid themselves in caves and in holes in the ground.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And although by their faith all these people won God's approval, none of them received the fulfilment of His great promise;
B058C011V040	58	11	40	for God had provided for them and us something better, so that apart from us they were not to attain to full blessedness.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore, surrounded as we are by such a vast cloud of witnesses, let us fling aside every encumbrance and the sin that so readily entangles our feet. And let us run with patient endurance the race that lies before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	simply fixing our gaze upon Jesus, our Prince Leader in the faith, who will also award us the prize. He, for the sake of the joy which lay before Him, patiently endured the cross, looking with contempt upon its shame, and afterwards seated Himself – where He still sits– at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	Therefore, if you would escape becoming weary and faint-hearted, compare your own sufferings with those of Him who endured such hostility directed against Him by sinners.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	In your struggle against sin you have not yet resisted so as to endanger your lives;
B058C012V005	58	12	5	and you have quite forgotten the encouraging words which are addressed to you as sons, and which say, 
B058C012V006	58	12	6	
        
B058C012V007	58	12	7	The sufferings that you are enduring are for your discipline. God is dealing with you as sons; for what son is there whom his father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	And if you are left without discipline, of which every true son has had a share, that shows that you are bastards, and not true sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Besides this, our earthly fathers used to discipline us and we treated them with respect, and shall we not be still more submissive to the Father of our spirits, and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	It is true that they disciplined us for a few years according as they thought fit; but He does it for our certain good, in order that we may become sharers in His own holy character.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	Now, at the time, discipline seems to be a matter not for joy, but for grief; yet it afterwards yields to those who have passed through its training a result full of peace–namely, righteousness.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore strengthen the drooping hands and paralysed knees,
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that what is lame may not be put entirely out of joint
B058C012V014	58	12	14	but may rather be restored. Persistently strive for peace with all men, and for that growth in holiness apart from which no one will see the Lord.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	Be carefully on your guard lest there be any one who falls back from the grace of God; lest any root bearing bitter fruit spring up and cause trouble among you, and through it the whole brotherhood be defiled;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	lest there be a fornicator, or an ungodly person like Esau, who, in return for a single meal, parted with the birthright which belonged to him.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that even afterwards, when he wished to secure the blessing, he was rejected; for he found no opportunity for undoing what he had done, though he sought the blessing earnestly with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to a material object all ablaze with fire, and to gloom and darkness and storm and trumpet-blast and the sound of words–
B058C012V019	58	12	19	a sound of such a kind that those who heard it entreated that no more should be added.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not endure the order which had been given, 
B058C012V021	58	12	21	and so terrible was the scene that Moses said, 
B058C012V022	58	12	22	On the contrary you have come to Mount Zion, and to the city of the ever-living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, to countless hosts of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	to the great festal gathering and Church of the first-born, whose names are recorded in Heaven, and to a Judge who is God of all, and to the spirits of righteous men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	and to Jesus the negotiator of a new Covenant, and to the sprinkled blood which speaks in more gracious tones than that of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	Be careful not to refuse to listen to Him who is speaking to you. For if they of old did not escape unpunished when they refused to listen to him who spoke on earth, much less shall we escape who turn a deaf ear to Him who now speaks from Heaven.
B058C012V026	58	12	26	His voice then shook the earth, but now we have His promise, 
B058C012V027	58	12	27	Here the words »Yet again, once for all« denote the removal of the things which can be shaken –created things– in order that the things which cannot be shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore, receiving, as we now do, a kingdom which cannot be shaken, let us cherish thankfulness so that we may ever offer to God an acceptable service, with godly reverence and awe.
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is also a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love always continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not neglect to show kindness to strangers; for, in this way, some, without knowing it, have had angels as their guests.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember prisoners, as if you were in prison with them; and remember those suffering ill-treatment, for you yourselves also are still in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Let marriage be held in honour among all, and let the marriage bed be unpolluted; for fornicators and adulterers God will judge.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Your lives should be untainted by love for money. Be content with what you have; for God Himself has said, 
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So that we fearlessly say, 
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your former leaders–it was they who brought you God's Message. Bear in mind how they ended their lives, and imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and to-day–yes, and to the ages to come.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be drawn aside by all sorts of strange teaching; for it is well to have the heart made stedfast through God's grace, and not by special kinds of food, from which those who scrupulously attend to them have derived no benefit.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We Christians have an altar from which the ministers of the Jewish Tent have no right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of those animals of which the blood is carried by the High Priest into the Holy place as an offering for sin, are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	And for this reason Jesus also, in order, by His own blood, to set the people free from sin, suffered outside the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Therefore let us go to Him outside the camp, sharing the insults directed against Him.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For we have no permanent city here, but we are longing for the city which is soon to be ours.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Through Him, then, let us continually lay on the altar a sacrifice of praise to God, namely, the utterance of lips that give thanks to His Name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	And do not forget to be kind and liberal; for with sacrifices of that sort God is greatly pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey your leaders and be submissive to them. For they are keeping watch over your souls as those who will have to give account; that they may do this with joy and not with lamentation. For that would be of no advantage to you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Keep on praying for us; for we are sure that we have clear consciences, and we desire to live nobly in every respect.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	I specially urge this upon you in order that I may be the more speedily restored to you.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may God who gives peace, and brought Jesus, our Lord, up again from among the dead –even Him who, by virtue of the blood of the eternal Covenant, is the great Shepherd of the sheep–
B058C013V021	58	13	21	fully equip you with every grace that you may need for the doing of His will, producing in us that which will truly please Him through Jesus Christ. To Him be the glory to the Ages of the Ages! Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	Bear with me, brethren, when I thus exhort you; for, in fact, it is but a short letter that I have written to you.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	You will rejoice to hear that our brother Timothy has been set at liberty. If he comes soon, I will see you with him.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all your leaders and all God's people. The brethren from Italy send you greetings.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all! Amen.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	James, a bondservant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ: to the twelve tribes who are scattered over the world. All good wishes.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Reckon it nothing but joy, my brethren, whenever you find yourselves hedged in by various trials.
B059C001V003	59	1	3	Be assured that the testing of your faith leads to power of endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	Only let endurance have perfect results so that you may become perfect and complete, deficient in nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	And if any one of you is deficient in wisdom, let him ask God for it, who gives with open hand to all men, and without upbraiding; and it will be given him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith and have no doubts; for he who has doubts is like the surge of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed into spray.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	A person of that sort must not expect to receive anything from the Lord–
B059C001V008	59	1	8	such a one is a man of two minds, undecided in every step he takes.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Let a brother in humble life rejoice when raised to a higher position;
B059C001V010	59	1	10	but a rich man should rejoice in being brought low, for like flowers among the herbage rich men will pass away.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	The sun rises with his scorching heat and dries up the herbage, so that its flowers drop off and the beauty of its appearance perishes, and in the same way rich men with all their prosperity will fade away.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is he who patiently endures trials; for when he has stood the test, he will gain the victor's crown –even the crown of Life– which the Lord has promised to those who love Him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no one say when passing through trial, »My temptation is from God;« for God is incapable of being tempted to do evil, and He Himself tempts no one.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But when a man is tempted, it is his own passions that carry him away and serve as a bait.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then the passion conceives, and becomes the parent of sin; and sin, when fully matured, gives birth to death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my dearly-loved brethren.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every gift which is good, and every perfect boon, is from above, and comes down from the Father, who is the source of all Light. In Him there is no variation nor the slightest suggestion of change.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	In accordance with His will He made us His children through the Message of the truth, so that we might, in a sense, be the Firstfruits of the things which He has created.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	You know this, my dearly-loved brethren. But let every one be quick to hear, slow to speak, and slow to be angry.
B059C001V020	59	1	20	For a man's anger does not lead to action which God regards as righteous.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Ridding yourselves, therefore, of all that is vile and of the evil influences which prevail around you, welcome in a humble spirit the Message implanted within you, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But prove yourselves obedient to the Message, and do not be mere hearers of it, imposing a delusion upon yourselves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if any one listens but does not obey, he is like a man who carefully looks at his own face in a mirror.
B059C001V024	59	1	24	Although he has looked carefully at himself, he goes away, and has immediately forgotten the sort of man he is.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But he who looks closely into the perfect Law –the Law of freedom– and continues looking, he, being not a hearer who forgets, but an obedient doer, will as the result of his obedience be blessed.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If a man thinks that he is scrupulously religious, although he is not curbing his tongue but is deceiving himself, his religious service is worthless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	The religious service which is pure and stainless in the sight of our God and Father is to visit fatherless children and widowed women in their time of trouble, and to keep one's own self unspotted from the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brethren, you must not make distinctions between one man and another while you are striving to maintain faith in the Lord Jesus Christ, who is our glory.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For suppose a man comes into one of your meetings wearing gold rings and fine clothes, and there also comes in a poor man wearing shabby clothes,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you pay court to the one who wears the fine clothes, and say, »Sit here; this is a good place;« while to the poor man you say, »Stand there, or sit on the floor at my feet;«
B059C002V004	59	2	4	is it not plain that in your hearts you have little faith, seeing that you have become judges full of wrong thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my dearly-loved brethren. Has not God chosen those whom the world regards as poor to be rich in faith and heirs of the Kingdom which He has promised to those that love Him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But 
B059C002V007	59	2	7	and the very people who speak evil of the noble Name by which you are called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	If, however, you are keeping the Law as supreme, in obedience to the Commandment which says 
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you are making distinctions between one man and another, you are guilty of sin, and are convicted by the Law as offenders.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	A man who has kept the Law as a whole, but has failed to keep some one command, has become guilty of violating all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For He who said, 
B059C002V012	59	2	12	Speak and act as those should who are expecting to be judged by the Law of freedom.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For he who shows no mercy will have judgement given against him without mercy; but mercy triumphs over judgement.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What good is it, my brethren, if a man professes to have faith, and yet his actions do not correspond? Can such faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	Suppose a Christian brother or sister is poorly clad or lacks daily food,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you says to them, »I wish you well; keep yourselves warm and well fed,« and yet you do not give them what they need; what is the use of that?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	So also faith, if it is unaccompanied by obedience, has no life in it–so long as it stands alone.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	Nay, some one will say, »You have faith, I have actions: prove to me your faith apart from corresponding actions and I will prove mine to you by my actions.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that God is one, and you are quite right: evil spirits also believe this, and shudder.«
B059C002V020	59	2	20	But, idle boaster, are you willing to be taught how it is that faith apart from obedience is worthless? Take the case of Abraham our forefather.
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was it, or was it not, because of his actions that he was declared to be righteous as the result of his having offered up his son Isaac upon the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You notice that his faith was co-operating with his actions, and that by his actions his faith was perfected;
B059C002V023	59	2	23	and the Scripture was fulfilled which says, 
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You all see that it is because of actions that a man is pronounced righteous, and not simply because of faith.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	In the same way also was not the notorious sinner Rahab declared to be righteous because of her actions when she welcomed the spies and hurriedly helped them to escape another way?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For just as a human body without a spirit is lifeless, so also faith is lifeless if it is unaccompanied by obedience.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	Do not be eager, my brethren, for many among you to become teachers; for you know that we teachers shall undergo severer judgement.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For we often stumble and fall, all of us. If there is any one who never stumbles in speech, that man has reached maturity of character and is able to curb his whole nature.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	Remember that we put the horses' bit into their mouths to make them obey us, and so we turn their whole bodies round.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	So too with ships, great as they are, and often driven along by strong gales, yet they can be steered with a very small rudder in whichever direction the caprice of the man at the helm chooses.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	In the same way the tongue is an insignificant part of the body, but it is immensely boastful. Remember how a mere spark may set a vast forest in flames.
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire. That world of iniquity, the tongue, is placed within us spotting and soiling our whole nature, and setting the whole round of our lives on fire, being itself set on fire by Gehenna.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For brute nature under all its forms –beasts and birds, reptiles and fishes– can be subjected and kept in subjection by human nature.
B059C003V008	59	3	8	But the tongue no man or woman is able to tame. It is an ever-busy mischief, and is full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless the Lord and Father, and with it we curse men, who are made in God's likeness.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	Out of the same mouth there proceed blessing and cursing. My brethren, this ought not to be.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	In a fountain, are fresh water and bitter sent forth from the same opening?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Can a fig-tree, my brethren, yield olives, or a vine yield figs? No; and neither can salt water yield sweet.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Which of you is a wise and well-instructed man? Let him prove it by a right life with conduct guided by a wisely teachable spirit.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if in your hearts you have bitter feelings of envy and rivalry, do not speak boastfully and falsely, in defiance of the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	That is not the wisdom which comes down from above: it belongs to earth, to the unspiritual nature, and to evil spirits.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where envy and rivalry are, there also are unrest and every vile deed.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	The wisdom from above is first of all pure, then peaceful, courteous, not self-willed, full of compassion and kind actions, free from favouritism and from all insincerity.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	And peace, for those who strive for peace, is the seed of which the harvest is righteousness.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	What causes wars and contentions among you? Is it not the cravings which are ever at war within you for various pleasures?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You covet things and yet cannot get them; you commit murder; you have passionate desires and yet cannot gain your end; you begin to fight and make war. You have not, because you do not pray;
B059C004V003	59	4	3	or you pray and yet do not receive, because you pray wrongly, your object being to waste what you get on some pleasure or another.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You unfaithful women, do you not know that friendship with the world means enmity to God? Therefore whoever is bent on being friendly with the world makes himself an enemy to God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you suppose that it is to no purpose that the Scripture says, »The Spirit which He has caused to dwell in our hearts yearns jealously over us«?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But He gives more abundant grace, as is implied in His saying, 
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Submit therefore to God: resist the Devil, and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God, and He will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners, and make your hearts pure, you who are half-hearted towards God.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Afflict yourselves and mourn and weep aloud; let your laughter be turned into grief, and your gladness into shame.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves in the presence of the Lord, and He will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak evil of one another, brethren. The man who speaks evil of a brother-man or judges his brother-man speaks evil of the Law and judges the Law. But if you judge the Law, you are no longer one who obeys the Law, but one who judges it.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	The only real Lawgiver and Judge is He who is able to save or to destroy. Who are you to sit in judgement on your fellow man?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come, you who say, »To-day or to-morrow we will go to this or that city, and spend a year there and carry on a successful business,«
B059C004V014	59	4	14	when, all the while, you do not even know what will happen to-morrow. For what is the nature of your life? Why, it is but a mist, which appears for a short time and then is seen no more.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	Instead of that you ought to say, »If it is the Lord's will, we shall live and do this or that.«
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But, as the case stands, it is in mere self-confidence that you boast: all such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	If, however, a man knows what it is right to do and yet does not do it, he commits a sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Come, you rich men, weep aloud and howl for your sorrows which will soon be upon you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your treasures have rotted, and your piles of clothing are moth-eaten;
B059C005V003	59	5	3	your gold and your silver have become covered with rust, and the rust on them will give evidence against you, and will eat your flesh like fire. You have hoarded up wealth in these last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	I tell you that the pay of the labourers who have gathered in your crops –pay which you are keeping back– is calling out against you; and the outcries of those who have been your reapers have entered into the ears of the Lord of the armies of Heaven.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	Here on earth you have lived self-indulgent and profligate lives. You have stupefied yourselves with gross feeding; but a day of slaughter has come.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned –you have murdered– the righteous man: he offers no resistance.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Be patient therefore, brethren, until the Coming of the Lord. Notice how eagerly a farmer waits for a valuable crop! He is patient over it till it has received the early and the later rain.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	So you also must be patient: keeping up your courage; for the Coming of the Lord is now close at hand.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not cry out in condemnation of one another, brethren, lest you come under judgement. I tell you that the Judge is standing at the door.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	In illustration, brethren, of persecution patiently endured take the Prophets who have spoken as messengers from the Lord.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Remember that we call those blessed who endured what they did. You have also heard of Job's patient endurance, and have seen the issue of the Lord's dealings with him–how full of tenderness and pity the Lord is.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But above all things, my brethren, do not swear, either by Heaven or by the earth, or with any other oath. Let your `yes' be simply `yes,' and your `no' be simply `no;' that you may not come under condemnation.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is one of you suffering? Let him pray. Is any one in good spirits? Let him sing a psalm.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is any one ill? Let him send for the Elders of the Church, and let them pray over him, after anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith will restore the sick man, and the Lord will raise him up to health; and if he has committed sins, they shall be forgiven.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Therefore confess your sins to one another, and pray for one another, so that you may be cured. The heartfelt supplication of a righteous man exerts a mighty influence.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man with a nature similar to ours, and he earnestly prayed that there might be no rain: and no rain fell on the land for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	Again he prayed, and the sky gave rain and the land yielded its crops.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	My brethren, if one of you strays from the truth and some one brings him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	let him know that he who brings a sinner back from his evil ways will save the man's soul from death and throw a veil over a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an Apostle of Jesus Christ: To God's own people scattered over the earth, who are living as foreigners in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Roman Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	chosen in accordance with the foreknowledge of God the Father, through the sanctifying work of the Spirit, with a view to their obedience and to their being sprinkled with the blood of Jesus Christ. May more and more grace and peace be granted to you.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who in His great mercy has begotten us anew to an ever-living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	to an inheritance imperishable, undefiled and unfading, which has been reserved in Heaven for you,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	whom God in His power is guarding through faith for a salvation that even now stands ready for unveiling at the End of the Age.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	Rejoice triumphantly in the prospect of this, even if now, for a short time, you are compelled to sorrow amid various trials.
B060C001V007	60	1	7	The sorrow comes in order that the testing of your faith –being more precious than that of gold, which perishes and yet is proved by fire– may be found to result in praise and glory and honour at the re-appearing of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V008	60	1	8	Him you love, though your eyes have never looked on Him. In Him, though at present you cannot see Him, you nevertheless trust, and triumph with a joy which is unspeakable and is crowned with glory,
B060C001V009	60	1	9	while you are securing as the outcome of your faith the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	There were Prophets who earnestly inquired about that salvation, and closely searched into it–even those who spoke beforehand of the grace which was to come to you.
B060C001V011	60	1	11	They were eager to know the time which the Spirit of Christ within them kept indicating, or the characteristics of that time, when they solemnly made known beforehand the sufferings that were to come upon Christ and the glories which would follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	To them it was revealed that they were serving not themselves but you, when they foretold the very things which have now been openly declared to you by those who, having been taught by the Holy Spirit which had been sent from Heaven, brought you the Good News. Angels long to stoop and look into these things.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore gird up your minds and fix your hopes calmly and unfalteringly upon the boon that is soon to be yours, at the re-appearing of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V014	60	1	14	And, since you delight in obedience, do not shape your lives by the cravings which used to dominate you in the time of your ignorance,
B060C001V015	60	1	15	but –in imitation of the holy One who has called you– you also must be holy in all your habits of life.
B060C001V016	60	1	16	Because it stands written, 
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you address as your Father Him who judges impartially in accordance with each man's actions, then spend in fear the time of your stay here on earth,
B060C001V018	60	1	18	knowing, as you do, that it was not with a ransom of perishable wealth, such as silver or gold, that you were set free from your frivolous habits of life which had been handed down to you from your forefathers,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with the precious blood of Christ–as of an unblemished and spotless lamb.
B060C001V020	60	1	20	He was pre-destined indeed to this work, even before the creation of the world, but has been plainly manifested in these last days for the sake of you who, through Him,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	are faithful to God, who raised Him from among the dead and gave Him glory, so that your faith and hope are resting upon God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Now that, through your obedience to the truth, you have purified your souls for cherishing sincere brotherly love, you must love another heartily and fervently.
B060C001V023	60	1	23	For you have been begotten again by God's ever-living and enduring word from a germ not of perishable, but of imperishable life.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	
        
B060C001V025	60	1	25	
        
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Rid yourselves therefore of all ill-will and all deceitfulness, of insincerity and envy, and of all evil speaking.
B060C002V002	60	2	2	Thirst, like newly-born infants, for pure milk for the soul, that by it you may grow up to salvation;
B060C002V003	60	2	3	if you have had any experience of the goodness of the Lord.
B060C002V004	60	2	4	Come to Him, the ever-living Stone, rejected indeed by men as worthless, but in God's esteem chosen and held in honour.
B060C002V005	60	2	5	And be yourselves also like living stones that are being built up into a spiritual house, to become a holy priesthood to offer spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	For it is contained in Scripture, 
B060C002V007	60	2	7	To you believers, therefore, that honour belongs; but for unbelievers– 
B060C002V008	60	2	8	and 
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a priesthood of kingly lineage, a holy nation, a people belonging specially to God, that you may make known the perfections of Him who called you out of darkness into His marvellous light.
B060C002V010	60	2	10	Once you were not a people, but now you are the people of God. Once you had not found mercy, but now you have.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Dear friends, I entreat you as pilgrims and foreigners not to indulge the cravings of your lower natures: for all such cravings wage war upon the soul.
B060C002V012	60	2	12	Live honourable lives among the Gentiles, in order that, although they now speak against you as evil-doers, they may yet witness your good conduct, and may glorify God on the day of reward and retribution.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Submit, for the Lord's sake, to every authority set up by man, whether it be to the Emperor as supreme ruler,
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to provincial Governors as sent by him for the punishment of evil-doers and the encouragement of those who do what is right.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For it is God's will that by doing what is right you should thus silence the ignorant talk of foolish persons.
B060C002V016	60	2	16	Be free men, and yet do not make your freedom an excuse for base conduct, but be God's bondservants.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honour every one. Love the brotherhood, fear God, honour the Emperor.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Household servants, be submissive to your masters, and show them the utmost respect–not only if they are kind and thoughtful, but also if they are unreasonable.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For it is an acceptable thing with God, if, from a sense of duty to Him, a man patiently submits to wrong, when treated unjustly.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	If you do wrong and receive a blow for it, what credit is there in your bearing it patiently? But if when you do right and suffer for it you bear it patiently, this is an acceptable thing with God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	And it is to this you were called; because Christ also suffered on your behalf, leaving you an example so that you should follow in His steps.
B060C002V022	60	2	22	He never sinned, and no deceitful language was ever heard from His mouth.
B060C002V023	60	2	23	When He was reviled, He did not answer with reviling; when He suffered He uttered no threats, but left His wrongs in the hands of the righteous Judge.
B060C002V024	60	2	24	The burden of our sins He Himself carried in His own body to the Cross and bore it there, so that we, having died so far as our sins are concerned, may live righteous lives. By His wounds yours have been healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were straying like lost sheep, but now you have come back to the Shepherd and Protector of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	Married women, in the same way, be submissive to your husbands, so that even if some of them disbelieve the Message, they may, apart from the Message, be won over by the daily life of their wives, after watching your daily life–
B060C003V002	60	3	2	so full of reverence, and so blameless!
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Your adornment ought not to be a merely outward thing–one of plaiting the hair, putting on jewelry, or wearing beautiful dresses.
B060C003V004	60	3	4	Instead of that, it should be a new nature within–the imperishable ornament of a gentle and peaceful spirit, which is indeed precious in the sight of God.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For in ancient times also this was the way the holy women who set their hopes upon God used to adorn themselves, being submissive to their husbands.
B060C003V006	60	3	6	Thus, for instance, Sarah obeyed Abraham, acknowledging his authority over her. And you have become Sarah's children if you do what is right and permit nothing whatever to terrify you.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	Married men, in the same way, live with your wives with a clear recognition of the fact that they are weaker than you. Yet, since you are heirs with them of God's free gift of Life, treat them with honour; so that your prayers may not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	In conclusion, all of you should be of one mind, quick to sympathize, kind to the brethren, tenderhearted, lowly-minded,
B060C003V009	60	3	9	not requiting evil with evil nor abuse with abuse, but, on the contrary, giving a blessing in return, because a blessing is what you have been called by God to inherit.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For 
B060C003V011	60	3	11	
        
B060C003V012	60	3	12	
        
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who will be able to harm you, if you show yourselves zealous for that which is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you suffer for righteousness' sake, you are to be envied. So do not be alarmed by their threats, nor troubled;
B060C003V015	60	3	15	but in your hearts consecrate Christ as Lord, being always ready to make your defence to any one who asks from you a reason for the hope which you cherish.
B060C003V016	60	3	16	Yet argue modestly and cautiously, keeping your consciences free from guilt, so that, when you are spoken against, those who slander your good Christian lives may be put to shame.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better that you should suffer for doing right, if such be God's will, than for doing evil;
B060C003V018	60	3	18	because Christ also once for all died for sins, the innocent One for the guilty many, in order to bring us to God. He was put to death in the flesh, but made alive in the spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	in which He also went and proclaimed His Message to the spirits that were in prison,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who in ancient times had been disobedient, while God's longsuffering was patiently waiting in the days of Noah during the building of the Ark, in which a few persons –eight in number– were brought safely through the water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	And, corresponding to that figure, the water of baptism now saves you –not the washing off of material defilement, but the craving of a good conscience after God– through the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who is at God's right hand, having gone into Heaven, angels and authorities and powers having been made subject to Him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Since, then, Christ has suffered in the flesh, you also must arm yourselves with a determination to do the same –because he who has suffered in the flesh has done with sin–
B060C004V002	60	4	2	that in future you may spend the rest of your earthly lives, governed not by human passions, but by the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For you have given time enough in the past to the doing of the things which the Gentiles delight in– pursuing, as you did, a course of habitual licence, debauchery, hard drinking, noisy revelry, drunkenness and unholy image-worship.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	At this they are astonished–that you do not run into the same excess of profligacy as they do; and they speak abusively of you.
B060C004V005	60	4	5	But they will have to give account to Him who stands ready to pronounce judgement on the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	For it is with this end in view that the Good News was proclaimed even to some who were dead, that they may be judged, as all mankind will be judged, in the body, but may be living a godly life in the spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	But the end of all things is now close at hand: therefore be sober-minded and temperate, so that you may give yourselves to prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all continue to love one another fervently, for love throws a veil over a multitude of faults.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Extend ungrudging hospitality towards one another.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	Whatever be the gifts which each has received, you must use them for one another's benefit, as good stewards of God's many-sided kindness.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If any one preaches, let it be as uttering God's truth; if any one renders a service to others, let it be in the strength which God supplies; so that in everything glory may be given to God in the name of Jesus Christ, to whom belong the glory and the might to the Ages of the Ages. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Dear friends, do not be surprised at finding that that scorching flame of persecution is raging among you to put you to the test–as though some surprising thing were accidentally happening to you.
B060C004V013	60	4	13	On the contrary, in the degree that you share in the sufferings of the Christ, rejoice, so that at the unveiling of His glory you may also rejoice with triumphant gladness.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	You are to be envied, if you are being reproached for bearing the name of Christ; for in that case the Spirit of glory – even the Spirit of God– is resting upon you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	But let not one of you suffer as a murderer or a thief or an evil-doer, or as a spy upon other people's business.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	If, however, any one suffers because he is a Christian, let him not be ashamed, but let him glorify God for being permitted to bear that name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time has come for judgement to begin, and to begin at the house of God; and if it begins with us, what will be the end of those who reject God's Good News?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And if it is difficult even for a righteous man to be saved, what will become of irreligious men and sinners?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Therefore also, let those who are suffering in accordance with the will of God entrust their souls in well-doing to a faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	So I exhort the Elders among you–I who am their fellow Elder and have been an eye-witness of the sufferings of the Christ, and am also a sharer in the glory which is soon to be revealed.
B060C005V002	60	5	2	Be shepherds of God's flock which is among you. Exercise the oversight not reluctantly but eagerly, in accordance with the will of God; not for base gain but with cheerful minds;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	not lording it over your Churches but proving yourselves patterns for the flock to imitate.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	And then, when the chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the never-withering wreath of glory.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	In the same way you younger men must submit to your elders; and all of you must gird yourselves with humility towards one another, for God sets Himself against the proud, but gives grace to the humble.
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Humble yourselves therefore beneath the mighty hand of God, so that at the right time He may set you on high.
B060C005V007	60	5	7	Throw the whole of your anxiety upon Him, because He Himself cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Curb every passion, and be on the alert. Your great accuser, the Devil, is going about like a roaring lion to see whom he can devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Withstand him, firm in your faith; knowing that your brethren in other parts of the world are passing through just the same experiences.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	And God, the giver of all grace, who has called you to share His eternal glory, through Christ, after you have suffered for a short time, will Himself make you perfect, firm, and strong.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To Him be all power unto the Ages of the Ages! Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	I send this short letter by Silas, our faithful brother –for such I regard him– in order to encourage you, and to bear witness that what I have told you is the true grace of God. In it stand fast.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	The Church in Babylon, chosen like yourselves by God, sends greetings, and so does Mark my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace be with all of you who are in Christ.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simon Peter, a bondservant and Apostle of Jesus Christ: To those to whom there has been allotted the same precious faith as that which is ours through the righteousness of our God and of our Saviour Jesus Christ.
B061C001V002	61	1	2	May more and more grace and peace be granted to you in a full knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord,
B061C001V003	61	1	3	seeing that His divine power has given us all things that are needful for life and godliness, through our knowledge of Him who has appealed to us by His own glorious perfections.
B061C001V004	61	1	4	It is by means of these that He has granted us His precious and wondrous promises, in order that through them you may, one and all, become sharers in the very nature of God, having completely escaped the corruption which exists in the world through earthly cravings.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	But for this very reason –adding, on your part, all earnestness– along with your faith, manifest also a noble character: along with a noble character, knowledge;
B061C001V006	61	1	6	along with knowledge, self-control; along with self-control, power of endurance;
B061C001V007	61	1	7	along with power of endurance, godliness; along with godliness, brotherly affection; and along with brotherly affection, love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	If these things exist in you, and continually increase, they prevent your being either idle or unfruitful in advancing towards a full knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For the man in whom they are lacking is blind and cannot see distant objects, in that he has forgotten that he has been cleansed from his old sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	For this reason, brethren, be all the more in earnest to make sure that God has called you and chosen you; for it is certain that so long as you practise these things, you will never stumble.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	And so a triumphant admission into the eternal Kingdom of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ will be freely granted to you.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	For this reason I shall always persist in reminding you of these things, although you know them and are stedfast believers in truth which you already possess.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	But I think it right, so long as I remain in the body, my present dwelling-place, to arouse you by such reminders.
B061C001V014	61	1	14	For I know that the time for me to lay aside my body is now rapidly drawing near, even as our Lord Jesus Christ has revealed to me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	So on every possible occasion I will also do my best to enable you to recall these things after my departure.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For when we made known to you the power and Coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, we were not eagerly following cleverly devised legends, but we had been eye-witnesses of His majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	He received honour and glory from God the Father, and out of the wondrous glory words such as these were spoken to Him, »This is My dearly-loved Son, in whom I take delight.«
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And we ourselves heard these words come from Heaven, when we were with Him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	And in the written word of prophecy we have something more permanent; to which you do well to pay attention –as to a lamp shining in a dimly-lighted place– until day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts.
B061C001V020	61	1	20	But, above all, remember that no prophecy in Scripture will be found to have come from the prophet's own prompting;
B061C001V021	61	1	21	for never did any prophecy come by human will, but men sent by God spoke as they were impelled by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But there were also false prophets among the people, as there will be teachers of falsehood among you also, who will cunningly introduce fatal divisions, disowning even the Sovereign Lord who has redeemed them, and bringing on themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And in their immoral ways they will have many eager disciples, through whom religion will be brought into disrepute.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	Thirsting for riches, they will trade on you with their canting talk. From of old their judgement has been working itself out, and their destruction has not been slumbering.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For God did not spare angels when they had sinned, but hurling them down to Tartarus consigned them to caves of darkness, keeping them in readiness for judgement.
B061C002V005	61	2	5	And He did not spare the ancient world, although He preserved Noah, a herald of righteousness, with seven others, when He brought a deluge on the world of the ungodly.
B061C002V006	61	2	6	He reduced to ashes the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah, and condemned them to overthrow, making them an example to people who might in future be living godless lives.
B061C002V007	61	2	7	But when righteous Lot was sore distressed by the gross misconduct of immoral men He rescued him.
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(For their lawless deeds were torture, day after day, to the pure soul of that righteous man–all that he saw and heard whilst living in their midst.)
B061C002V009	61	2	9	Since all this is so, the Lord knows how to rescue godly men from temptation, and on the other hand how to keep the unrighteous under punishment in readiness for the Day of Judgement,
B061C002V010	61	2	10	and especially those who are abandoned to sensuality–craving, as they do, for polluted things, and scorning control. Fool-hardy and self-willed, they do not tremble when speaking evil of glorious beings;
B061C002V011	61	2	11	while angels, though greater than they in might and power, do not bring any insulting accusation against such in the presence of the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these men, like brute beasts, created (with their natural instincts) only to be captured or destroyed, are abusive in matters of which they are ignorant, and in their corruption will perish,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	being doomed to receive a requital for their guilt. They reckon it pleasure to feast daintily in broad daylight. They are spots and blemishes, while feeding luxuriously at their love-feasts, and banqueting with you.
B061C002V014	61	2	14	Their very eyes are full of adultery–being eyes which never cease from sin. These men set traps to catch unstedfast souls, their own hearts being well trained in greed. They are fore-doomed to God's curse!
B061C002V015	61	2	15	Forsaking the straight road, they have gone astray, having eagerly followed in the steps of Balaam, the son of Beor, who was bent on securing the wages of unrighteousness.
B061C002V016	61	2	16	But he was rebuked for his transgression: a dumb ass spoke with a human voice and checked the madness of the Prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These people are wells without water, mists driven along by a storm, men for whom the dense darkness has been reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For, while they pour out their frivolous and arrogant talk, they use earthly cravings –every kind of immorality– as a bait to entrap men who are just escaping from the influence of those who live in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	And they promise them freedom, although they are themselves the slaves of what is corrupt. For a man is the slave of any one by whom he has been worsted in fight.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after escaping from the pollutions of the world through a full knowledge of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ, people are once more entangled in these pollutions and are overcome, their last state has become worse than their first.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it would have been better for them not to have fully known the way of righteousness, than, after knowing it, to turn back from the holy commandments in which they were instructed.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	Their case is that described in the true proverb, 
B061C003V001	61	3	1	This letter which I am now writing to you, dear friends, is my second letter. In both my letters I seek to revive in your honest minds the memory of certain things,
B061C003V002	61	3	2	so that you may recall the words spoken long ago by the holy Prophets, and the commandments of our Lord and Saviour given you through your Apostles.
B061C003V003	61	3	3	But, above all, remember that, in the last days, men will come who make a mock at everything–men governed only by their own passions,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and, asking, »What has become of His promised Return? For from the time our forefathers fell asleep all things continue as they have been ever since the creation of the world.«
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For they are wilfully blind to the fact that there were heavens which existed of old, and an earth, the latter arising out of water and extending continuously through water, by the command of God;
B061C003V006	61	3	6	and that, by means of these, the then existing race of men was overwhelmed with water and perished.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But the present heavens and the present earth are, by the command of the same God, kept stored up, reserved for fire in preparation for a day of judgement and of destruction for the ungodly.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But there is one thing, dear friends, which you must not forget. With the Lord one day resembles a thousand years and a thousand years resemble one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slow in fulfilling His promise, in the sense in which some men speak of slowness. But He bears patiently with you, His desire being that no one should perish but that all should come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	The day of the Lord will come like a thief–it will be a day on which the heavens will pass away with a rushing noise, the elements be destroyed in the fierce heat, and the earth and all the works of man be utterly burnt up.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Since all these things are thus pre-destined to dissolution, what sort of men ought you to be found to be in all holy living and godly conduct,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	eagerly looking forward to the coming of the day of God, by reason of which the heavens, all ablaze, will be destroyed, and the elements will melt in the fierce heat?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But in accordance with His promise we are expecting new heavens and a new earth, in which righteousness will dwell.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, dear friends, since you have these expectations, earnestly seek to be found in His presence, free from blemish or reproach, in peace.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	And always regard the patient forbearance of our Lord as salvation, as our dear brother Paul also has written to you in virtue of the wisdom granted to him.
B061C003V016	61	3	16	That is what he says in all his letters, when speaking in them of these things. In those letters there are some statements hard to understand, which ill-taught and unprincipled people pervert, just as they do the rest of the Scriptures, to their own ruin.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You, therefore, dear friends, having been warned beforehand, must continually be on your guard so as not to be led astray by the false teaching of immoral men nor fall from your own stedfastness.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But be always growing in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ. To Him be all glory, both now and to the day of Eternity!
B062C001V001	62	1	1	That which was from the beginning, which we have listened to, which we have seen with our own eyes, and our own hands have handled concerning the Word of Life–
B062C001V002	62	1	2	the Life was manifested, and we have seen and bear witness, and we declare unto you the Life of the Ages which was with the Father and was manifested to us–
B062C001V003	62	1	3	that which we have seen and listened to we now announce to you also, in order that you also may have fellowship in it with us, and this fellowship with us is fellowship with the Father and with His Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And we write these things in order that our joy may be made complete.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This is the Message which we have heard from the Lord Jesus and now deliver to you–God is Light, and in Him there is no darkness.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If, while we are living in darkness, we profess to have fellowship with Him, we speak falsely and are not adhering to the truth.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we live in the light as He is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus, His Son, cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we claim to be already free from sin, we lead ourselves astray and the truth has no place in our hearts.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, He is so faithful and just that He forgives us our sins and cleanses us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we deny that we have sinned, we make Him a liar, and His Message has no place in our hearts.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	Dear children, I write thus to you in order that you may not sin. If any one sins, we have an Advocate with the Father–Jesus Christ the righteous;
B062C002V002	62	2	2	and He is an atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we may know that we know Him–if we obey His commands.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He who professes to know Him, and yet does not obey His commands, is a liar, and the truth has no place in his heart.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever obeys His Message, in him love for God has in very deed reached perfection. By this we can know that we are in Him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	The man who professes to be continuing in Him is himself also bound to live as He lived.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	My dearly-loved friends, it is no new command that I am now giving you, but an old command which you have had from the very beginning. By the old command I mean the teaching which you have already received.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	And yet I 
B062C002V009	62	2	9	Any one who professes to be in the light and yet hates his brother man is still in darkness.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loves his brother man continues in the light, and his life puts no stumbling-block in the way of others.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But he who hates his brother man is in darkness and is walking in darkness; and he does not know where he is going–because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I am writing to you, dear children, because for His sake your sins are forgiven you.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers, because you know Him who has existed from the very beginning. I am writing to you, young men, because you have overcome the Evil one. I have written to you, children, because you know the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, fathers, because you know Him who has existed from the very beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong and God's Message still has a place in your hearts, and you have overcome the Evil one.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world, nor the things in the world. If any one loves the world, there is no love in his heart for the Father.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For the things in the world –the cravings of the earthly nature, the cravings of the eyes, the show and pride of life– they all come, not from the Father, but from the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world, with its cravings, is passing away, but he who does God's will continues for ever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Dear children, the last hour has come; and as you once heard that there was to be an anti-Christ, so even now many anti-Christs have appeared. By this we may know that the last hour has come.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They have gone forth from our midst, but they did not really belong to us; for had they belonged to us, they would have remained with us. But they left us that it might be manifest that professed believers do not all belong to us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	As for you, you have an anointing from the holy One and have perfect knowledge.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have written to you, not because you are ignorant of the truth, but because you know it, and you know that nothing false comes from the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar compared with him who denies that Jesus is the Christ? He who disowns the Father and the Son is the anti-Christ.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	No one who disowns the Son has the Father. He who acknowledges the Son has also the Father.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	As for you, let the teaching which you have received from the very beginning continue in your hearts. If that teaching does continue in your hearts, you also will continue to be in union with the Son and with the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise which He Himself has given us–the Life of the Ages.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	I have thus written to you concerning those who are leading you astray.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	And as for you, the anointing which you received from Him remains within you, and there is no need for any one to teach you. But since His anointing gives you instruction in all things –and is true and is no falsehood– you are continuing in union with Him even as it has taught you to do.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, dear children, continue in union with Him; so that, if He re-appears, we may have perfect confidence, and may not shrink away in shame from His presence at His Coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	Since you know that He is righteous, be assured also that the man who habitually acts righteously is a child of His.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	See what marvellous love the Father has bestowed upon us –that we should be called God's children: and that is what we are. For this reason the world does not recognize us– because it has not known Him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Dear friends, we are now God's children, but what we are to be in the future has not yet been fully revealed. We know that if Christ reappears we shall be like Him, because we shall see Him as He is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And every man who has this hope fixed on Him, purifies himself so as to be as pure as He is.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Every one who is guilty of sin is also guilty of violating Law; for sin is the violation of Law.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that He appeared in order to take away sins; and in Him there is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	No one who continues in union with Him lives in sin: no one who lives in sin has seen Him or knows Him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Dear children, let no one lead you astray. The man who acts righteously is righteous, just as He is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He who is habitually guilty of sin is a child of the Devil, because the Devil has been a sinner from the very beginning. The Son of God appeared for the purpose of undoing the work of the Devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	No one who is a child of God is habitually guilty of sin. A God-given germ of life remains in him, and he cannot habitually sin–because he is a child of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	By this we can distinguish God's children and the Devil's children: no one who fails to act righteously is a child of God, nor he who does not love his brother man.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the Message you have heard from the beginning–that we are to love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	We are not to resemble Cain, who was a child of the Evil one and killed his own brother. And why did he kill him? Because his own actions were wicked and his brother's actions righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not be surprised, brethren, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	As for us, we know that we have already passed out of death into Life–because we love our brother men. He who is destitute of love continues dead.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Every one who hates his brother man is a murderer; and you know that no murderer has the Life of the Ages continuing in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	We know what love is–through Christ's having laid down His life on our behalf; and in the same way we ought to lay down our lives for our brother men.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But if any one has this world's wealth and sees that his brother man is in need, and yet hardens his heart against him–how can such a one continue to love God?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	Dear children, let us not love in words only nor with the lips, but in deed and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And in this way we shall come to know that we are loyal to the truth, and shall satisfy our consciences in His presence
B062C003V020	62	3	20	in whatever matters our hearts condemn us–because God is greater than our hearts and knows everything.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Dear friends, if our hearts do not condemn us, we have perfect confidence towards God;
B062C003V022	62	3	22	and whatever we ask for we obtain from Him, because we obey His commands and do the things which are pleasing in His sight.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is His command–that we are to believe in His Son Jesus Christ and love one another, just as He has commanded us to do.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	The man who obeys His commands continues in union with God, and God continues in union with him; and through His Spirit whom He has given us we can know that He continues in union with us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Dear friends, do not believe every spirit, but put the spirits to the test to see whether they are from God; for many false teachers have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	The test by which you may recognize the Spirit of God is that every spirit which acknowledges that Jesus Christ has come as man is from God,
B062C004V003	62	4	3	and that no spirit is from God which does not acknowledge this about Jesus. Such is the spirit of the anti-Christ; of whose coming you have heard, and it is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	As for you, dear children, you are God's children, and have successfully resisted them; for greater is He who is in you than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are the world's children, and so their language is that of the world, and the world listens to them. We are God's children.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	The man who is beginning to know God listens to us, but he who is not a child of God does not listen to us. By this test we can distinguish the Spirit of truth from the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Dear friends, let us love one another; for love has its origin in God, and every one who loves has become a child of God and is beginning to know God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He who is destitute of love has never had any knowledge of God; because God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	God's love for us has been manifested in that He has sent His only Son into the world so that we may have Life through Him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	This is love indeed–we did not love God, but He loved us and sent His Son to be an atoning sacrifice for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Dear friends, if God has so loved us, we also ought to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has ever yet seen God. If we love one another, God continues in union with us, and His love in all its perfection is in our hearts.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	We can know that we are continuing in union with Him and that He is continuing in union with us, by the fact that He has given us a portion of His Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and bear witness that the Father has sent the Son to be the Saviour of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God–God continues in union with him, and he continues in union with God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And, as for us, we know the love which God has for us, and we confide in it. God is love, and he who continues to love continues in union with God, and God continues in union with him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	Our love will be manifested in all its perfection by our having complete confidence on the day of the Judgement; because just what He is, we also are in the world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	Love has in it no element of fear; but perfect love drives away fear, because fear involves pain, and if a man gives way to fear, there is something imperfect in his love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love because God first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If any one says that he loves God, while he hates his brother man, he is a liar; for he who does not love his brother man whom he has seen, cannot love God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And the command which we have from Him is that he who loves God must love his brother man also.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Every one who believes that Jesus is the Christ is a child of God; and every one who loves the Father loves also Him who is the Father's Child.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	The fact that we love God Himself, and obey His commands, is a proof that we love God's children.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	Love for God means obedience to His commands; and His commands are not irksome.
B062C005V004	62	5	4	For every child of God overcomes the world; and the victorious principle which has overcome the world is our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who but the man that believes that Jesus is the Son of God overcomes the world?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	Jesus Christ is He who came with water and blood; not with the water only, but with the water and with the blood. And it is the Spirit who gives testimony– because the Spirit is the Truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three that give testimony– the Spirit, the water, and the blood;
B062C005V008	62	5	8	and there is complete agreement between these three.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we accept the testimony of men, God's testimony is greater: for God's testimony consists of the things which He has testified about His Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in his own heart: he who does not believe God has made Him a liar, in that he has refused to accept the testimony which God has given about His Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And that testimony is to the effect that God has given us the Life of the Ages, and that this Life is in His Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He who has the Son has the Life: he who has not the Son of God has not the Life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	I write all this to you in order that you who believe in the Son of God may know for certain that you already have the Life of the Ages.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And we have an assured confidence that whenever we ask anything in accordance with His will, He listens to us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And since we know that He listens to us, then whatever we ask, we know that we have the things which we have asked from Him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If any one sees a brother man committing a sin which is not unto death, he shall ask and God shall give him life–for those who do not sin unto death. There is such a thing as sin unto death; for that I do not bid him make request.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	Any kind of wrongdoing is sin; but there is sin which is not unto death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that no one who is a child of God lives in sin, but He who is God's Child keeps him, and the Evil one cannot touch him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are children of God, and that the whole world lies in the power of the Evil one.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of God has come, and has given us understanding so that we know the true One, and are in union with the true One–that is, we are in union with His Son Jesus Christ. He is the true God and the Life of the Ages.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Dear children, guard yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	The Elder to the elect lady and her children. Truly I love you all, and not I alone, but also all who know the truth,
B063C001V002	63	1	2	for the sake of the truth which is continually in our hearts and will be with us for ever.
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy and peace will be with us from God the Father, and from Jesus Christ the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	It is an intense joy to me to have found some of your children living true Christian lives, in obedience to the command which we have received from the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now, dear lady, I pray you –writing to you, as I do, not a new command, but the one which we have had from the very beginning– let us love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	The love of which I am speaking consists in our living in obedience to God's commands. God's command is that you should live in obedience to what you all heard from the very beginning.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have gone out into the world–men who do not acknowledge Jesus as Christ who has come in human nature. Such a one is `the deceiver' and `the anti-Christ.'
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Keep guard over yourselves, so that you may not lose the results of your good deeds, but may receive back a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	No one has God, who instead of remaining true to the teaching of Christ, presses on in advance: but he who remains true to that teaching has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If any one who comes to you does not bring this teaching, do not receive him under your roof nor bid him Farewell.
B063C001V011	63	1	11	He who bids him Farewell is a sharer in his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	I have a great deal to say to you all, but will not write it with paper and ink. Yet I hope to come to see you and speak face to face, so that your happiness may be complete.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your elect sister send greetings to you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	The Elder to his dear friend Gaius. Truly I love you.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	My dear friend, I pray that you may in all respects prosper and enjoy good health, just as your soul already prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For it is an intense joy to me when brethren come and bear witness to your fidelity to the truth–that you live in obedience to the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than to hear that my children are living in obedience to the truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	My dear friend, you are acting faithfully in all your behaviour towards the brethren, even when they are strangers to you.
B064C001V006	64	1	6	They have testified, in the presence of the Church, to your love; and you will do well to help them on their journey in a manner worthy of your fellowship with God.
B064C001V007	64	1	7	For it is for Christ that they have gone forth, accepting nothing from the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	It is therefore our duty to show hospitality to such men, so that we may be fellow workers in promoting the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote to the Church, but Diotrephes, who loves to have the first place among them, refuses to listen to us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	For this reason, if I come, I shall not forget his conduct, nor his idle and mischievous talk against us. And he does not stop there: he not only will not receive the brethren, but those who desire to do this he hinders, and excludes them from the Church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	My dear friend, do not follow wrong examples, but right ones. He who habitually does what is right is a child of God: he who habitually does what is wrong has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	The character of Demetrius has the approval of all men, and of the truth itself. We also express our approval of it, and you know that we only give our approval to that which is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I have a great deal to say to you, but I do not wish to go on writing it with ink and pen.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I hope to see you very soon, and then we will speak face to face. Peace be with you. Our friends send greetings to you. Greet our friends individually.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, a bondservant of Jesus Christ and a brother of James: To those who are in God the Father, enfolded in His love, and kept for Jesus Christ, and called.
B065C001V002	65	1	2	May mercy, peace and love be abundantly granted to you.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Dear friends, since I am eager to begin a letter to you on the subject of our common salvation, I find myself constrained to write and cheer you on to the vigorous defense of the faith delivered once for all to God's people.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain persons have crept in unnoticed –men spoken of in ancient writings as pre-destined to this condemnation– ungodly men, who pervert the grace of our God into an excuse for immorality, and disown Jesus Christ, our only Sovereign and Lord.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	I desire to remind you –although the whole matter is already familiar to you– that the Lord saved a people out of the land of Egypt, but afterwards destroyed those who had no faith.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And angels –those who did not keep the position originally assigned to them, but deserted their own proper abode– He reserves in everlasting bonds, in darkness, in preparation for the judgement of the great day.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	So also Sodom and Gomorrah –and the neighboring towns in the same manner– having been guilty of gross fornication and having gone astray in pursuit of unnatural vice, are now before us as a specimen of the fire of the Ages in the punishment which they are undergoing.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Yet in just the same way these dreamers also pollute the body, while they set authority at naught and speak evil of dignities.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	But Michael the Archangel, when contending with the Devil and arguing with him about the body of Moses, did not dare to pronounce judgement on him in abusive terms, but simply said, »The Lord rebuke you.«
B065C001V010	65	1	10	Yet these men are abusive in matters of which they know nothing, and in things which, like the brutes, they understand instinctively–in all these they corrupt themselves.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Alas for them; for they have followed in the steps of Cain; for the sake of gain they have rushed on headlong in the evil ways of Balaam; and have perished in rebellion like that of Korah!
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These men –sunken rocks!– are those who share the pleasure of your love-feasts, unrestrained by fear while caring only for themselves; clouds without water, driven away by the winds; trees that cast their fruit, barren, doubly dead, uprooted;
B065C001V013	65	1	13	wild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom is reserved dense darkness of age-long duration.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	It was also about these that Enoch, who belonged to the seventh generation from Adam, prophesied, saying, »The Lord has come, attended by myriads of His people, to execute judgement upon all,
B065C001V015	65	1	15	and to convict all the ungodly of all the ungodly deeds which in their ungodliness they have committed, and of all the hard words which they, ungodly sinners as they are, have spoken against Him.«
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These men are murmurers, ever bemoaning their lot. Their lives are guided by their evil passions, and their mouths are full of big, boastful words, while they treat individual men with admiring reverence for the sake of the advantage they can gain.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But as for you, my dearly-loved friends, remember the words that before now were spoken by the Apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ–
B065C001V018	65	1	18	how they declared to you, »In the last times there shall be scoffers, obeying only their own ungodly passions.«
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are those who cause divisions. They are men of the world, wholly unspiritual.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, my dearly-loved friends, building yourselves up on the basis of your most holy faith and praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	must keep yourselves safe in the love of God, waiting for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ which will result in the Life of the Ages.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	Some, when they argue with you, you must endeavor to convince;
B065C001V023	65	1	23	others you must try to save, as brands plucked from the flames; and on others look with pity mingled with fear, while you hate every trace of their sin.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	But to Him who is able to keep you safe from stumbling, and cause you to stand in the presence of His glory free from blemish and full of exultant joy–
B065C001V025	65	1	25	to the only God our Saviour–through Jesus Christ our Lord, be ascribed glory, majesty, might, and authority, as it was before all time, is now, and shall be to all the Ages! Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	The revelation given by Jesus Christ, which God granted Him, that He might make known to His servants certain events which must shortly come to pass: and He sent His angel and communicated it to His servant John.
B066C001V002	66	1	2	This is the John who taught the truth concerning the Word of God and the truth told us by Jesus Christ– a faithful account of what he had seen.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who reads and blessed are those who listen to the words of this prophecy and lay to heart what is written in it; for the time for its fulfillment is now close at hand.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John sends greetings to the seven Churches in the province of Asia. May grace be granted to you, and peace, from Him who is and was and evermore will be; and from the seven Spirits which are before His throne;
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ, the truthful witness, the first of the dead to be born to Life, and the Ruler of the kings of the earth. To Him who loves us and has freed us from our sins with His own blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and has formed us into a Kingdom, to be priests to God, His Father–to Him be ascribed the glory and the power until the Ages of the Ages. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	He is coming in the clouds, and every eye will see Him, and so will those who pierced Him; and all the nations of the earth will gaze on Him and mourn. Even so. Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	»I am the Alpha and the Omega,« says the Lord God, »He who is and was and evermore will be–the Ruler of all.«
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I John, your brother, and a sharer with you in the sorrows and Kingship and patient endurance of Jesus, found myself in the island of Patmos, on account of the Word of God and the truth told us by Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	In the Spirit I found myself present on the day of the Lord, and I heard behind me a loud voice which resembled the blast of a trumpet.
B066C001V011	66	1	11	It said, »Write forthwith in a roll an account of what you see, and send it to the seven Churches–to Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyateira, Sardis, Philadelphia and Laodicea.«
B066C001V012	66	1	12	I turned to see who it was that was speaking to me; and then I saw seven golden lampstands,
B066C001V013	66	1	13	and in the center of the lampstands some One resembling the Son of Man, clothed in a robe which reached to His feet, and with a girdle of gold across His breast.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and His hair were white, like white wool–as white as snow; and His eyes resembled a flame of fire.
B066C001V015	66	1	15	His feet were like silver-bronze, when it is white-hot in a furnace; and His voice resembled the sound of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	In His right hand He held seven stars, and a sharp, two-edged sword was seen coming from His mouth; and His glance resembled the sun when it is shining with its full strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	When I saw Him, I fell at His feet as if I were dead. But He laid His right hand upon me and said, »Do not be afraid: I am the First and the Last, and the ever-living One.
B066C001V018	66	1	18	I died; but I am now alive until the Ages of the Ages, and I have the keys of the gates of Death and of Hades!
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Write down therefore the things you have just seen, and those which are now taking place, and those which are soon to follow:
B066C001V020	66	1	20	the secret meaning of the seven stars which you have seen in My right hand, and of the seven lampstands of gold. The seven stars are the ministers of the seven Churches, and the seven lampstands are the seven Churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	»To the minister of the Church in Ephesus write as follows:« `This is what He who holds the seven stars in the grasp of His right hand says–He who walks to and fro among the seven lampstands of gold.
B066C002V002	66	2	2	I know your doings and your toil and patient suffering. And I know that you cannot tolerate wicked men, but have put to the test those who say that they themselves are Apostles but are not, and you have found them to be liars.
B066C002V003	66	2	3	And you endure patiently and have borne burdens for My sake and have never grown weary.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	Yet I have this against you–that you no longer love Me as you did at first.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Be mindful, therefore, of the height from which you have fallen. Repent at once, and act as you did at first, or else I will surely come and remove your lampstand out of its place–unless you repent.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	Yet this you have in your favor: you hate the doings of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.
B066C002V007	66	2	7	»`Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches. To him who overcomes I will give the privilege of eating the fruit of the Tree of Life, which is in the Paradise of God.'«
B066C002V008	66	2	8	»To the minister of the Church at Smyrna write as follows:« `This is what the First and the Last says–He who died and has returned to life.
B066C002V009	66	2	9	Your sufferings I know, and your poverty –but you are rich– and the evil name given you by those who say that they themselves are Jews, and are not, but are Satan's synagogue.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Dismiss your fears concerning all that you are about to suffer. I tell you that the Devil is about to throw some of you into prison that you may be put to the test, and for ten days you will have to endure persecution. Be faithful to the End, even if you have to die, and then I will give you the victor's Wreath of Life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	»`Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches. He who overcomes shall be in no way hurt by the Second Death.'«
B066C002V012	66	2	12	»To the minister of the Church at Pergamum write as follows:« `This is what He who has the sharp, two-edged sword says. I know where you dwell.
B066C002V013	66	2	13	Satan's throne is there; and yet you are true to Me, and did not deny your faith in Me, even in the days of Antipas My witness and faithful friend, who was put to death among you, in the place where Satan dwells.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	Yet I have a few things against you, because you have with you some that cling to the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to put a stumbling-block in the way of the descendants of Israel–to eat what had been sacrificed to idols, and commit fornication.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	So even you have some that cling in the same way to the teaching of the Nicolaitans.
B066C002V016	66	2	16	Repent, at once; or else I will come to you quickly, and will make war upon them with the sword which is in My mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	»`Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches. He who overcomes –to him I will give some of the hidden Manna, and a white stone; and– written upon the stone and known only to him who receives it– a new name.'«
B066C002V018	66	2	18	»To the minister of the Church at Thyateira write as follows:« `This is what the Son of God says–He who has eyes like a flame of fire, and feet resembling silver-bronze.
B066C002V019	66	2	19	I know your doings, your love, your faith, your service, and your patient endurance; and that of late you have toiled harder than you did at first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	Yet I have this against you, that you tolerate the woman Jezebel, who calls herself a prophetess and by her teaching leads astray My servants, so that they commit fornication and eat what has been sacrificed to idols.
B066C002V021	66	2	21	I have given her time to repent, but she is determined not to repent of her fornication.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	I tell you that I am about to cast her upon a bed of sickness, and I will severely afflict those who commit adultery with her, unless they repent of conduct such as hers.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	Her children too shall surely die; and all the Churches shall come to know that I am He who searches into men's inmost thoughts; and to each of you I will give a requital which shall be in accordance with what your conduct has been.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But to you, the rest of you in Thyateira, all who do not hold this teaching and are not the people who have learnt the »deep things,« as they call them (the deep things of Satan!) –to you I say that I lay no other burden on you.
B066C002V025	66	2	25	Only that which you already possess, cling to until I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	»`And to him who overcomes and obeys My commands to the very end, I will give authority over the nations of the earth.
B066C002V027	66	2	27	And he shall be their shepherd, ruling them with a rod of iron, just as earthenware jars are broken to pieces; and his power over them shall be like that which I Myself have received from My Father;«
B066C002V028	66	2	28	and I will give him the Morning Star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches.'
B066C003V001	66	3	1	»To the minister of the Church at Sardis write as follows:« `This is what He who has the seven Spirits of God and the seven stars says. I know your doings–you are supposed to be alive, but in reality you are dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Rouse yourself and keep awake, and strengthen those things which remain but have well-nigh perished; for I have found no doings of yours free from imperfection in the sight of My God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Be mindful, therefore, of the lessons you have received and heard. Continually lay them to heart, and repent. If, however, you fail to rouse yourself and keep awake, I shall come upon you suddenly like a thief, and you will certainly not know the hour at which I shall come to judge you.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	Yet you have in Sardis a few who have not soiled their garments; and they shall walk with Me in white; for they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	»`In this way he who overcomes shall be clothed in white garments; and I will certainly not blot out his name from the Book of Life, but will acknowledge him in the presence of My Father and His angels.«
B066C003V006	66	3	6	Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches.'
B066C003V007	66	3	7	»To the minister of the Church at Philadelphia write as follows:« `This is what the holy One and the true says –He who has the key of David– He who opens and no one shall shut, and shuts and no one shall open.
B066C003V008	66	3	8	I know your doings. I have put an opened door in front of you, which no one can shut; because you have but a little power, and yet you have guarded My word and have not disowned Me.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	I will cause some belonging to Satan's synagogue who say that they themselves are Jews, and are not, but are liars–I will make them come and fall at your feet and know for certain that I have loved you.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because in spite of suffering you have guarded My word, I in turn will guard you from that hour of trial which is soon coming upon the whole world, to put to the test the inhabitants of the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	I am coming quickly: cling to that which you already possess, so that your wreath of victory be not taken away from you.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	»`He who overcomes–I will make him a pillar in the sanctuary of My God, and he shall never go out from it again. And I will write on him the name of My God, and the name of the city of My God, the new Jerusalem, which is to come down out of Heaven from My God, and My own new name.«
B066C003V013	66	3	13	Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches.'
B066C003V014	66	3	14	»And to the minister of the Church at Laodicea write as follows:« `This is what the Amen says–the true and faithful witness, the Beginning and Lord of God's Creation.
B066C003V015	66	3	15	I know your doings–you are neither cold nor hot; I would that you were cold or hot!
B066C003V016	66	3	16	Accordingly, because you are lukewarm and neither hot nor cold, before long I will vomit you out of My mouth.
B066C003V017	66	3	17	You say, I am rich, and have wealth stored up, and I stand in need of nothing; and you do not know that if there is a wretched creature it is 
B066C003V018	66	3	18	Therefore I counsel you to buy of Me gold refined in the fire that you may become rich, and white robes to put on, so as to hide your shameful nakedness, and eye-salve to anoint your eyes with, so that you may be able to see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	All whom I hold dear, I reprove and chastise; therefore be in earnest and repent.
B066C003V020	66	3	20	I am now standing at the door and am knocking. If any one listens to My voice and opens the door, I will go in to be with him and will feast with him, and he shall feast with Me.
B066C003V021	66	3	21	»`To him who overcomes I will give the privilege of sitting down with Me on My throne, as I also have overcome and have sat down with My Father on His throne.
B066C003V022	66	3	22	Let all who have ears give heed to what the Spirit is saying to the Churches.'«
B066C004V001	66	4	1	After all this I looked and saw a door in Heaven standing open, and the voice that I had previously heard, which resembled the blast of a trumpet, again spoke to me and said, »Come up here, and I will show you things which are to happen in the future.«
B066C004V002	66	4	2	Immediately I found myself in the Spirit, and saw a throne in Heaven, and some One sitting on the throne.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	The appearance of Him who sat there was like jasper or sard; and encircling the throne was a rainbow, in appearance like an emerald.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	Surrounding the throne there were also twenty-four other thrones, on which sat twenty-four Elders clothed in white robes, with victors' wreaths of gold upon their heads.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	Out from the throne there came flashes of lightning, and voices, and peals of thunder, while in front of the throne seven blazing lamps were burning, which are the seven Spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And in front of the throne there seemed to be a sea of glass, resembling crystal. And midway between the throne and the Elders, and surrounding the throne, were four living creatures, full of eyes in front and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	The first living creature resembled a lion, the second an ox, the third had a face like that of a man, and the fourth resembled an eagle flying.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And each of the four living creatures had six wings, and in every direction, and within, are full of eyes; and day after day, and night after night, they never cease saying, »Holy, holy, holy, Lord God, the Ruler of all, who wast and art and evermore shalt be.«
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And whenever the living creatures give glory and honor and thanks to Him who is seated on the throne, and lives until the Ages of the Ages,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the twenty-four Elders fall down before Him who sits on the throne and worship Him who lives until the Ages of the Ages, and they cast their wreaths down in front of the throne,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	saying, »It is fitting, O our Lord and God, That we should ascribe unto Thee the glory and the honor and the power; For Thou didst create all things, And because it was Thy will they came into existence, and were created.«
B066C005V001	66	5	1	And I saw lying in the right hand of Him who sat on the throne a book written on both sides and closely sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	And I saw a mighty angel who was exclaiming in a loud voice, »Who is worthy to open the book and break its seals?«
B066C005V003	66	5	3	But no one in Heaven, or on earth, or under the earth, was able to open the book or look into it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And while I was weeping bitterly, because no one was found worthy to open the book or look into it,
B066C005V005	66	5	5	one of the Elders said to me, »Do not weep. The Lion which belongs to the tribe of Judah, the Root of David, has triumphed, and will open the book and break its seven seals.«
B066C005V006	66	5	6	Then, midway between the throne and the four living creatures, I saw a Lamb standing among the Elders. He looked as if He had been offered in sacrifice, and He had seven horns and seven eyes. The last-named are the seven Spirits of God, and have been sent far and wide into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	So He comes, and now He has taken the book out of the right hand of Him who is seated on the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	And when He had taken the book, the four living creatures and the twenty-four Elders fell down before the Lamb, having each of them a harp and bringing golden bowls full of incense, which represent the prayers of God's people.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	And now they sing a new song. »It is fitting,« they say, »that Thou shouldst be the One to take the book And break its seals; Because Thou hast been offered in sacrifice, And hast purchased for God with Thine own blood Some out of every tribe and language and people and nation,
B066C005V010	66	5	10	And hast formed them into a Kingdom to be priests to our God, And they reign over the earth.«
B066C005V011	66	5	11	And I looked, and heard what seemed to be the voices of countless angels on every side of the throne, and of the living creatures and the Elders. Their number was myriads of myriads and thousands of thousands,
B066C005V012	66	5	12	and in loud voices they were singing, »It is fitting that the Lamb which has been offered in sacrifice should receive all power and riches and wisdom and might and honor and glory and blessing.«
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And as for every created thing in Heaven and on earth and under the earth and on the sea, and everything that was in any of these, I heard them say, »To Him who is seated on the throne, And to the Lamb, Be ascribed all blessing and honor And glory and might, Until the Ages of the Ages!«
B066C005V014	66	5	14	Then the four living creatures said »Amen,« and the Elders fell down and worshipped.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	And when the Lamb broke one of the seven seals I saw it, and I heard one of the four living creatures say, as if in a voice of thunder, »Come.«
B066C006V002	66	6	2	And I looked and a white horse appeared, and its rider carried a bow; and a victor's wreath was given to him; and he went out conquering and in order to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	And when the Lamb broke the second seal, I heard the second living creature say, »Come.«
B066C006V004	66	6	4	And another horse came out–a fiery-red one; and power was given to its rider to take peace from the earth, and to cause men to kill one another; and a great sword was given to him.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	When the Lamb broke the third seal, I heard the third living creature say, »Come.« I looked, and a black horse appeared, its rider carrying a balance in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	And I heard what seemed to be a voice speaking in the midst of the four living creatures, and saying, »A quart of wheat for a shilling, and three quarts of barley for a shilling; but do not injure either the oil or the wine.«
B066C006V007	66	6	7	When the Lamb broke the fourth seal I heard the voice of the fourth living creature say, »Come.«
B066C006V008	66	6	8	I looked and a pale-colored horse appeared. Its rider's name was Death, and Hades came close behind him; and authority was given to them over the fourth part of the earth, to kill with the sword or with famine or pestilence or by means of the wild beasts of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	When the Lamb broke the fifth seal, I saw at the foot of the altar the souls of those whose lives had been sacrificed because of the word of God and of the testimony which they had given.
B066C006V010	66	6	10	And now in loud voices they cried out, saying, »How long, O Sovereign Lord, the holy One and the true, dost Thou delay judgment and the taking of vengeance upon the inhabitants of the earth for our blood?«
B066C006V011	66	6	11	And there was given to each of them a long white robe, and they were bidden to wait patiently for a short time longer, until the full number of their fellow bondservants should also complete–namely of their brethren who were soon to be killed just as they had been.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	When the Lamb broke the sixth seal I looked, and there was a great earthquake, and the sun became as dark as sackcloth, and the whole disc of the moon became like blood.
B066C006V013	66	6	13	The stars in the sky also fell to the earth, as when a fig-tree, upon being shaken by a gale of wind, casts its unripe figs to the ground.
B066C006V014	66	6	14	The sky too passed away, as if a scroll were being rolled up, and every mountain and island was removed from its place.
B066C006V015	66	6	15	The kings of the earth and the great men, the military chiefs, the wealthy and the powerful –all, whether slaves or free men– hid themselves in the caves and in the rocks of the mountains,
B066C006V016	66	6	16	while they called to the mountains and the rocks, saying, »Fall on us and hide us from the presence of Him who sits on the throne and from the anger of the Lamb;
B066C006V017	66	6	17	for the day of His anger –that great day– has come, and who is able to stand?«
B066C007V001	66	7	1	After this I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth, and holding back the four winds of the earth so that no wind should blow over the earth or the sea or upon any tree.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	And I saw another angel coming from the east and carrying a seal belonging to the ever-living God. He called in a loud voice to the four angels whose work it was to injure the earth and the sea.
B066C007V003	66	7	3	»Injure neither land nor sea nor trees,« he said, »until we have sealed the bondservants of our God upon their foreheads.«
B066C007V004	66	7	4	When the sealing was finished, I heard how many were sealed out of the tribes of the descendants of Israel. They were 144,000.
B066C007V005	66	7	5	Of the tribe of Judah, 12,000 were sealed; Of the tribe of Reuben, 12,000; Of the tribe of Gad, 12,000;
B066C007V006	66	7	6	Of the tribe of Asher, 12,000; Of the tribe of Naphtali, 12,000; Of the tribe of Manasseh, 12,000;
B066C007V007	66	7	7	Of the tribe of Symeon, 12,000; Of the tribe of Levi, 12,000; Of the tribe of Issachar, 12,000;
B066C007V008	66	7	8	Of the tribe of Zebulun, 12,000; Of the tribe of Joseph, 12,000; Of the tribe of Benjamin, 12,000.
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After this I looked, and a vast host appeared which it was impossible for anyone to count, gathered out of every nation and from all tribes and peoples and languages, standing before the throne and before the Lamb, clothed in long white robes, and carrying palm-branches in their hands.
B066C007V010	66	7	10	In loud voices they were exclaiming, »It is to our God who is seated on the throne, and to the Lamb, that we owe our salvation!«
B066C007V011	66	7	11	All the angels were standing in a circle round the throne and round the Elders and the four living creatures, and they fell on their faces in front of the throne and worshipped God.
B066C007V012	66	7	12	»Even so!« they cried:»The blessing and the glory and the wisdom and the thanks and the honor and the power and the might are to be ascribed to our God, until the Ages of the Ages! Even so!«
B066C007V013	66	7	13	Then, addressing me, one of the Elders said, »Who are these people clothed in the long white robes? And where have they come from?«
B066C007V014	66	7	14	»My lord, you know,« I replied. »They are those,« he said, »who have just passed through the great distress, and have washed their robes and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.
B066C007V015	66	7	15	For this reason they stand before the very throne of God, and render Him service, day after day and night after night, in His sanctuary, and He who is sitting upon the throne will shelter them in His tent.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They will never again be hungry or thirsty, and never again will the sun or any scorching heat trouble them.
B066C007V017	66	7	17	For the Lamb who is in front of the throne will be their Shepherd, and will guide them to watersprings of Life, and God will wipe every tear from their eyes.«
B066C008V001	66	8	1	When the Lamb broke the seventh seal, there was silence in Heaven for about half an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	Then I saw the seven angels who are in the presence of God, and seven trumpets were given to them.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	And another angel came and stood close to the altar, carrying a censer of gold; and abundance of incense was given to him that he might place it with the prayers of all God's people upon the golden altar which was in front of the throne.
B066C008V004	66	8	4	And the smoke of the incense rose into the presence of God from the angel's hand, and mingled with the prayers of His people.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	So the angel took the censer and filled it with fire from the altar and flung it to the earth; and there followed peals of thunder, and voices, and flashes of lightning, and an earthquake.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	Then the seven angels who had the seven trumpets made preparations for blowing them.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	The first blew his trumpet; and there came hail and fire, mixed with blood, falling upon the earth; and a third part of the earth was burnt up, and a third part of the trees and all the green grass.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	The second angel blew his trumpet; and what seemed to be a great mountain, all ablaze with fire, was hurled into the sea; and a third part of the sea was turned into blood.
B066C008V009	66	8	9	And a third part of the creatures that were in the sea –those that had life– died; and a third part of the ships were destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	The third angel blew his trumpet; and there fell from Heaven a great star, which was on fire like a torch. It fell upon a third part of the rivers and upon the springs of water.
B066C008V011	66	8	11	The name of the star is `Wormwood;' and a third part of the waters were turned into wormwood, and vast numbers of the people died from drinking the water, because it had become bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	Then the fourth angel blew his trumpet; and a curse fell upon a third part of the sun, a third part of the moon, and a third part of the stars, so that a third part of them were darkened and for a third of the day, and also of the night, there was no light.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	Then I looked, and I heard a solitary eagle crying in a loud voice, as it flew across the sky, »Alas, alas, alas, for the inhabitants of the earth, because of the significance of the remaining trumpets which the three angels are about to blow!«
B066C009V001	66	9	1	The fifth angel blew his trumpet; and I saw a Star which had fallen from Heaven to the earth; and to him was given the key of the depths of the bottomless pit,
B066C009V002	66	9	2	and he opened the depths of the bottomless pit. And smoke came up out of the pit resembling the smoke of a vast furnace, so that the sun was darkened, and the air also, by reason of the smoke of the pit.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	And from the midst of the smoke there came locusts on to the earth, and power was given to them resembling the power which earthly scorpions possess.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	And they were forbidden to injure the herbage of the earth, or any green thing, or any tree. They were only to injure human beings–those who have not the seal of God on their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	Their mission was not to kill, but to cause awful agony for five months; and this agony was like that which a scorpion inflicts when it stings a man.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	And at that time people will seek death, but will by no possibility find it, and will long to die, but death evades them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	The appearance of the locusts was like that of horses equipped for war. On their heads they had wreaths which looked like gold.
B066C009V008	66	9	8	Their faces seemed human and they had hair like women's hair, but their teeth resembled those of lions.
B066C009V009	66	9	9	They had breast-plates which seemed to be made of steel; and the noise caused by their wings was like that of a vast number of horses and chariots hurrying into battle.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	They had tails like those of scorpions, and also stings; and in their tails lay their power of injuring mankind for five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	The locusts had a king over them–the angel of the bottomless pit, whose name in Hebrew is `Abaddon,' while in the Greek he is called `Apollyon.'
B066C009V012	66	9	12	The first woe is past; two other woes have still to come.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	The sixth angel blew his trumpet; and I heard a single voice speaking from among the horns of the golden incense altar which is in the presence of God.
B066C009V014	66	9	14	It said to the sixth angel–the angel who had the trumpet, »Set at liberty the four angels who are prisoners near the great river Euphrates.«
B066C009V015	66	9	15	And the four angels who had been kept in readiness for that hour, day, month, and year, were set at liberty, so that they might kill a third part of mankind.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	The number of the cavalry was two hundred millions; I heard their number.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	And this was the appearance of the horses which I saw in my vision–and of their riders. The body-armour of the riders was red, blue and yellow; and the horses' heads were shaped like the heads of lions, while from their mouths there came fire and smoke and sulphur.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	By these three plagues a third part of mankind were destroyed–by the fire and the smoke, and by the sulphur which came from their mouths.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	For the power of the horses is in their mouths and in their tails; their tails being like serpents, and having heads, and it is with them that they inflict injury.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	But the rest of mankind who were not killed by these plagues, did not even then repent and leave the things they had made, so as to cease worshipping the demons, and the idols of gold and silver, bronze, stone, and wood, which can neither see nor hear, nor move.
B066C009V021	66	9	21	Nor did they repent of their murders, their practice of magic, their fornication, or their thefts.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	Then I saw another strong angel coming down from Heaven. He was robed in a cloud, and over his head was the rainbow. His face was like the sun, and his feet resembled pillars of fire.
B066C010V002	66	10	2	In his hand he held a small scroll unrolled; and, planting his right foot on the sea and his left foot on the land,
B066C010V003	66	10	3	he cried out in a loud voice which resembled the roar of a lion. And when he had cried out, each of the seven peals of thunder uttered its own message.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	And when the seven peals of thunder had spoken, I was about to write down what they had said; but I heard a voice from Heaven which told me to keep secret all that the seven peals of thunder had said, and not write it down.
B066C010V005	66	10	5	Then the angel that I saw standing on the sea and on the land, lifted his right hand toward Heaven.
B066C010V006	66	10	6	And in the name of Him who lives until the Ages of the Ages, the Creator of Heaven and all that is in it, of the earth and all that is in it, and of the sea and all that is in it, he solemnly declared,
B066C010V007	66	10	7	»There shall be no further delay; but in the days when the seventh angel blows his trumpet –when he begins to do so– then the secret purposes of God are realized, in accordance with the good news which He gave to His servants the Prophets.«
B066C010V008	66	10	8	Then the voice which I had heard speaking from Heaven once more addressed me. It said, »Go and take the little book which lies open in the hand of the angel who is standing on the sea and on the land.«
B066C010V009	66	10	9	So I went to the angel and asked him to give me the little book. »Take it,« he said, »and eat the whole of it. You will find it bitter when you have eaten it, although in your mouth it will taste as sweet as honey.«
B066C010V010	66	10	10	So I took the roll out of the angel's hand and ate the whole of it; and in my mouth it was as sweet as honey, but when I had eaten it I found it very bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	And a voice said to me, »You must prophesy yet further concerning peoples, nations, languages, and many kings.«
B066C011V001	66	11	1	Then a reed was given me to serve as a measuring rod; and a voice said, »Rise, and measure God's sanctuary –and the altar– and count the worshipers who are in it.
B066C011V002	66	11	2	But as for the court which is outside the sanctuary, pass it over. Do not measure it; for it has been given to the Gentiles, and for forty-two months they will trample the holy city under foot.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	And I will authorize My two witnesses to prophesy for 1,260 days, clothed in sackcloth.
B066C011V004	66	11	4	»These witnesses are the two olive-trees, and they are the two lamps which stand in the presence of the Lord of the earth.«
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if any one seeks to injure them–fire comes from their mouths and devours their enemies; and if any one seeks to injure them, he will in this way certainly be killed.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	They have power given to them to seal up the sky, so that no rain may fall so long as they continue to prophesy; and power over the waters to turn them into blood, and to smite the earth with various plagues whenever they choose to do so.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	»And when they have fully delivered their testimony, the Wild Beast which is to rise out of the bottomless pit will make war upon them and overcome them and kill them.
B066C011V008	66	11	8	And their dead bodies are to lie in the broad street of the great city which spiritually is designated `Sodom' and `Egypt,' where indeed their Lord was crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	And men belonging to all peoples, tribes, languages and nations gaze at their dead bodies for three days and a half, but they refuse to let them be laid in a tomb.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	The inhabitants of the earth rejoice over them and are glad and will send gifts to one another; for these two Prophets had greatly troubled the inhabitants of the earth.«
B066C011V011	66	11	11	But at the end of the three days and a half the breath of life from God entered into them, and they rose to their feet; and all who saw them were terrified.
B066C011V012	66	11	12	Then they heard a loud voice calling to them out of Heaven, and bidding them come up; and they went up to Heaven in the cloud, and their enemies saw them go.
B066C011V013	66	11	13	And just as that time there was a great earthquake, and a tenth part of the city was overthrown. 7,000 people were killed in the earthquake, and the rest were terrified and gave glory to the God of Heaven.
B066C011V014	66	11	14	The second Woe is past; the third Woe will soon be here.
B066C011V015	66	11	15	The seventh angel blew his trumpet; and there followed loud voices in Heaven which said, »The sovereignty of the world now belongs to our Lord and His Christ; and He will be King until the Ages of the Ages.«
B066C011V016	66	11	16	Then the twenty-four Elders, who sit on thrones in the presence of God, fell on their faces and worshipped God,
B066C011V017	66	11	17	saying, »We give thee thanks, O Lord God, the Ruler of all, Who art and wast, because Thou hast exerted Thy power, Thy great power, and hast become King.
B066C011V018	66	11	18	The nations grew angry, and Thine anger has come, and the time for the dead to be judged, and the time for Thee to give their reward to Thy servants the Prophets and to Thy people, and to those who fear Thee, the small and the great, and to destroy those who destroy the earth.«
B066C011V019	66	11	19	Then the doors of God's sanctuary in Heaven were opened, and the Ark, in which His Covenant was, was seen in His sanctuary; and there came flashes of lightning, and voices, and peals of thunder, and an earthquake, and heavy hail.
B066C012V001	66	12	1	And a great marvel was seen in Heaven– a woman who was robed with the sun and had the moon under her feet, and had also a wreath of stars round her head, was with child,
B066C012V002	66	12	2	and she was crying out in the pains and agony of childbirth.
B066C012V003	66	12	3	And another marvel was seen in Heaven–a great fiery-red Dragon, with seven heads and ten horns; and on his heads were seven kingly crowns.
B066C012V004	66	12	4	His tail was drawing after it a third part of the stars of Heaven, and it dashed them to the ground. And in front of the woman who was about to become a mother, the Dragon was standing in order to devour the child as soon as it was born.
B066C012V005	66	12	5	She gave birth to a son–a male child, destined before long to rule all nations with an iron scepter. But her child was caught up to God and His throne,
B066C012V006	66	12	6	and the woman fled into the Desert, there to be cared for, for 1,260 days, in a place which God had prepared for her.
B066C012V007	66	12	7	And war broke out in Heaven, Michael and his angels engaging in battle with the Dragon.
B066C012V008	66	12	8	The Dragon fought and so did his angels; but they were defeated, and there was no longer any room found for them in Heaven.
B066C012V009	66	12	9	The great Dragon, the ancient serpent, he who is called `the Devil' and `the Adversary' and leads the whole earth astray, was hurled down: he was hurled down to the earth, and his angels were hurled down with him.
B066C012V010	66	12	10	Then I heard a loud voice speaking in Heaven. It said, »The salvation and the power and the Kingdom of our God have now come, and the sovereignty of His Christ; for the accuser of our brethren has been hurled down–he who, day after day and night after night, was wont to accuse them in the presence of God.
B066C012V011	66	12	11	But they have gained the victory over him because of the blood of the Lamb and of the testimony which they have borne, and because they held their lives cheap and did not shrink even from death.
B066C012V012	66	12	12	For this reason be glad, O Heaven, and you who live in Heaven! Alas for the earth and the sea! For the Devil has come down to you; full of fierce anger, because he knows that his appointed time is short.«
B066C012V013	66	12	13	And when the Dragon saw that he was hurled down to the earth, he went in pursuit of the woman who had given birth to the male child.
B066C012V014	66	12	14	Then, the two wings of a great eagle were given to the woman to enable her to fly away into the Desert to the place assigned her, there to be cared for, for a period of time, two periods of time, and half a period of time, beyond the reach of the serpent.
B066C012V015	66	12	15	And the serpent poured water from his mouth –a very river it seemed– after the woman, in the hope that she would be carried away by its flood.
B066C012V016	66	12	16	But the earth came to the woman's help: it opened its mouth and drank up the river which the Dragon had poured from his mouth.
B066C012V017	66	12	17	This made the Dragon furiously angry with the woman, and he went elsewhere to make war upon her other children–those who keep God's commandments and hold fast to the testimony of Jesus.
B066C013V001	66	13	1	And he took up a position upon the sands of the sea-shore. Then I saw a Wild Beast coming up out of the sea, and he had ten horns and seven heads. On his horns were ten kingly crowns, and inscribed on his heads were names full of blasphemy.
B066C013V002	66	13	2	The Wild Beast which I saw resembled a leopard, and had feet like the feet of a bear, and his mouth was like the mouth of a lion; and it was to the Dragon that he owed his power and his throne and his wide dominion.
B066C013V003	66	13	3	I saw that one of his heads seemed to have been mortally wounded; but his mortal wound was healed, and the whole world was amazed and followed him.
B066C013V004	66	13	4	And they offered worship to the Dragon, because it was to him that the Wild Beast owed his dominion; and they also offered worship to the Wild Beast, and said, »Who is there like him? And who is able to engage in battle with him?«
B066C013V005	66	13	5	And there was given him a mouth full of boastful and blasphemous words; and liberty of action was granted him for forty-two months.
B066C013V006	66	13	6	And he opened his mouth to utter blasphemies against God, to speak evil of His name and of His dwelling-place–that is to say, of those who dwell in Heaven.
B066C013V007	66	13	7	And permission was given him to make war upon God's people and conquer them; and power was given him over every tribe, people, language and nation.
B066C013V008	66	13	8	And all the inhabitants of the earth will be found to be worshipping him: every one whose name is not recorded in the Book of Life–the Book of the Lamb who has been offered in sacrifice ever since the creation of the world.
B066C013V009	66	13	9	Let all who have ears give heed.
B066C013V010	66	13	10	If any one is eager to lead others into captivity, he must himself go into captivity. If any one is bent on killing with the sword, he must himself be killed by the sword. Here is an opportunity for endurance, and for the exercise of faith, on the part of God's people.
B066C013V011	66	13	11	Then I saw another Wild Beast, coming up out of the earth. He had two horns like those of a lamb, but he spoke like a dragon.
B066C013V012	66	13	12	And the authority of the first Wild Beast –the whole of that authority– he exercises in his presence, and he causes the earth and its inhabitants to worship the first Wild Beast, whose mortal wound had been healed.
B066C013V013	66	13	13	He also works great miracles, so as even to make fire come down from Heaven to earth in the presence of human beings.
B066C013V014	66	13	14	And his power of leading astray the inhabitants of the earth is due to the marvels which he has been permitted to work in the presence of the Wild Beast. And he told the inhabitants of the earth to erect a statue to the Wild Beast who had received the sword-stroke and yet had recovered.
B066C013V015	66	13	15	And power was granted him to give breath to the statue of the Wild Beast, so that the statue of the Wild Beast could even speak and cause all who refuse to worship it to be put to death.
B066C013V016	66	13	16	And he causes all, small and great, rich and poor, free men and slaves, to have stamped upon them a mark on their right hands or on their foreheads,
B066C013V017	66	13	17	in order that no one should be allowed to buy or sell unless he had the mark–either the name of the Wild Beast or the number which his name represents.
B066C013V018	66	13	18	Here is scope for ingenuity. Let people of shrewd intelligence calculate the number of the Wild Beast; for it indicates a certain man, and his number is 666.
B066C014V001	66	14	1	Then I looked, and I saw the Lamb standing upon Mount Zion, and with Him 144,000 people, having His name and His Father's name written on their foreheads.
B066C014V002	66	14	2	And I heard music from Heaven which resembled the sound of many waters and the roar of loud thunder; and the music which I heard was like that of harpists playing upon their harps.
B066C014V003	66	14	3	And they were singing what seemed to be a new song, in front of the throne and in the presence of the four living creatures and the Elders; and no one was able to learn that song except the 144,000 people who had been redeemed out of the world.
B066C014V004	66	14	4	These are those who had not defiled themselves with women: they are as pure as virgins. They follow the Lamb wherever He goes. They have been redeemed from among men, as firstfruits to God and to the Lamb.
B066C014V005	66	14	5	And no lie has ever been found upon their lips: they are faultless.
B066C014V006	66	14	6	And I saw another angel flying across the sky, carrying the Good News of the Ages to tell to every nation, tribe, language and people, among those who live on the earth.
B066C014V007	66	14	7	He said in a loud voice, »Fear God and give Him glory, because the time of His judgment has come; and worship Him who made sky and earth, the sea and the water-springs.«
B066C014V008	66	14	8	And another, a second angel, followed, exclaiming, »Great Babylon has fallen, has fallen–she who made all the nations drink the wine of the anger provoked by her fornication.«
B066C014V009	66	14	9	And another, a third angel, followed them, exclaiming in a loud voice, »If any one worships the Wild Beast and his statue, and receives a mark on his forehead or on his hand,
B066C014V010	66	14	10	he shall drink the wine of God's anger which stands ready, undiluted, in the cup of His fury, and he shall be tormented with fire and sulphur in the presence of the holy angels and of the Lamb.
B066C014V011	66	14	11	And the smoke of their torment goes up until the Ages of the Ages; and the worshipers of the Wild Beast and his statue have no rest day or night, nor has any one who receives the mark of his name.
B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is an opportunity for endurance on the part of God's people, who carefully keep His commandments and the faith of Jesus!«
B066C014V013	66	14	13	And I heard a voice speaking from Heaven. It said, »Write as follows: »`Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord from this time onward. Yes, says the Spirit, let them rest from their sorrowful labours; for what they have done goes with them.'«
B066C014V014	66	14	14	Then I looked, and a white cloud appeared, and sitting on the cloud was some One resembling the Son of Man, having a wreath of gold upon His head and in His hand a sharp sickle.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	And another, an angel, came out of the sanctuary, calling in a loud voice to Him who sat on the cloud, and saying, »Use your sickle and reap the harvest, for the hour for reaping it has come: the harvest of the earth is over-ripe.«
B066C014V016	66	14	16	Then He who sat on the cloud flung His sickle on the earth, and the earth had its harvest reaped.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	And another angel came out from the sanctuary in Heaven, and he too carried a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	And another angel came out from the altar –he who had power over fire– and he spoke in a loud voice to him who had the sharp sickle, saying, »Use your sharp sickle, and gather the bunches from the vine of the earth, for its grapes are now quite ripe.«
B066C014V019	66	14	19	And the angel flung his sickle down to the earth, and reaped the vine of the earth and threw the grapes into the great winepress of God's anger.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	And the winepress was trodden outside the city, and out of it came blood reaching the horses' bridles for a distance of 200 miles.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	Then I saw another marvel in Heaven, great and wonderful–there were seven angels bringing seven plagues. These are the last plagues, because in them God's anger has found full expression.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw what seemed to be a sea of glass mingled with fire, and those who had gained the victory over the Wild Beast and over his statue and the number of his name, standing by the sea of glass and having harps which belonged to God.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they were singing the song of Moses, God's servant, and the song of the Lamb. Their words were, »Great and wonderful are Thy works, O Lord God, the Ruler of all. Righteous and true are Thy ways, O King of the nations.
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not be afraid, O Lord, and glorify Thy name? For Thou alone art holy. All nations shall come and shall worship Thee, because the righteousness of all that Thou hast done has been made manifest.«
B066C015V005	66	15	5	After this, when the doors of the sanctuary of the tent of witness in Heaven were opened, I looked;
B066C015V006	66	15	6	and there came out of the sanctuary the seven angels who were bringing the seven plagues. The angels were clad in pure, bright linen, and had girdles of gold across their breasts.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four living creatures gave the seven angels seven bowls of gold, full of the anger of God who lives until the Ages of the Ages.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the sanctuary was filled with smoke from the glory of God and from His power; and no one could enter the sanctuary till the seven plagues brought by the seven angels were at an end.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	Then I heard a loud voice from the sanctuary say to the seven angels, »Go and pour on to the earth the seven bowls of the anger of God.«
B066C016V002	66	16	2	So the first angel went away and poured his bowl on to the earth; and it brought a bad and painful sore upon the men who had on them the mark of the Wild Beast and worshipped his statue.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	The second angel poured his bowl into the sea, and it became blood, like a dead man's blood, and every living creature in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	The third angel poured his bowl into the rivers and springs of water, and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters say, »Righteous art Thou, who art and wast, the holy One, because Thou hast thus taken vengeance.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	For they poured out the blood of Thy people and of the Prophets, and in return Thou hast given them blood to drink. And this they deserved.«
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard a voice from the altar say, »Even so, O Lord God, the Ruler of all, true and righteous are Thy judgments.«
B066C016V008	66	16	8	Then the fourth angel poured his bowl on to the sun, and power was given to it to scorch men with fire.
B066C016V009	66	16	9	And the men were severely burned; and yet they spoke evil of God who had power over the plagues, and they did not repent so as to give Him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	The fifth angel poured his bowl on to the throne of the Wild Beast; and his kingdom became darkened. People gnawed their tongues because of the pain,
B066C016V011	66	16	11	and they spoke evil of the God in Heaven because of their pains and their sores, and did not repent of their misconduct.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	The sixth angel poured his bowl into that great river, the Euphrates; and its stream was dried up in order to clear the way for the kings who are to come from the east.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	Then I saw three foul spirits, resembling frogs, issue from the mouth of the Dragon, from the mouth of the Wild Beast, and from the mouth of the false Prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are the spirits of demons working marvels–spirits that go out to control the kings of the whole earth, to assemble them for the battle which is to take place on the great day of God, the Ruler of all.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	(»I am coming like a thief. Blessed is the man who keeps awake and guards his raiment for fear he walk about ill-clad, and his uncomeliness become manifest.«)
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And assemble them they did at the place called in Hebrew `Har-Magedon.'
B066C016V017	66	16	17	Then the seventh angel poured his bowl into the air; and a loud voice came out of the sanctuary from the throne, saying, »Everything is now ready.«
B066C016V018	66	16	18	Flashes of lightning followed, and voices, and peals of thunder, and an earthquake more dreadful than there had ever been since there was a man upon the earth–so terrible was it, and so great!
B066C016V019	66	16	19	The great city was split into three parts; the cities of the nations fell; and great Babylon came into remembrance before God, for Him to make her drink from the wine-cup of His fierce anger.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	Every island fled away, and there was not a mountain anywhere to be seen.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And heavy hail, that seemed to be a talent in weight, fell from the sky upon the people; and they spoke evil of God on account of the plague of the hail–because the plague of it was exceedingly severe.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	Then one of the seven angels who were carrying the seven bowls came and spoke to me. »Come with me,« he said, »and I will show you the doom of the great Harlot who sits upon many waters.
B066C017V002	66	17	2	The kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the inhabitants of the earth have been made drunk with the wine of her fornication.«
B066C017V003	66	17	3	So he carried me away in the Spirit into a desert, and there I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet-colored Wild Beast which was covered with names of blasphemy and had seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	The woman was clothed in purple and scarlet, and was brilliantly attired with gold and jewels and pearls. She held in her hand a cup of gold, full of abominations, and she gave filthy indications of her fornication.
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And on her forehead was a name written:»I am a symbol of great Babylon, the mother of the harlots and of the abominations of the earth.«
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drinking herself drunk with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the witnesses of Jesus. And when I saw her I was filled with utter astonishment.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	Then the angel said to me, »Why are you so astonished? I will explain to you the secret meaning of the woman and of the seven-headed, ten-horned Wild Beast which carries her.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	»The Wild Beast which you have seen was, and is not, and yet is destined to re-ascend, before long, out of the bottomless pit and go his way into perdition. And the inhabitants of the earth will be filled with amazement –all whose names are not in the Book of Life, having been recorded there ever since the creation of the world– when they see the Wild Beast: because he was, and is not, and yet is to come.«
B066C017V009	66	17	9	Here is scope for the exercise of a mind that has wisdom! The seven heads are the seven hills on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And they are seven kings: five of them have fallen, and the one is still reigning. The seventh has not yet come, but when he comes he must continue for a short time.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the Wild Beast which once existed but does not now exist–he is an eighth king and yet is one of the seven and he goes his way into perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	»And the ten horns which you have seen are ten kings who have not yet come to the throne, but for a single hour they are to receive authority as kings along with the Wild Beast.«
B066C017V013	66	17	13	They have one common policy, and they are to give their power and authority to the Wild Beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	They will make war upon the Lamb, and the Lamb will triumph over them; for He is Lord of lords and King of kings. And those who accompany Him –called, as they are, and chosen, and faithful– shall share in the victory.«
B066C017V015	66	17	15	He also said to me, »The waters which you have seen, on which the Harlot sits, are peoples and multitudes, nations and languages.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns that you have seen –and the Wild Beast– these will hate the Harlot, and they will cause her to be laid waste and will strip her bare. They will eat her flesh, and burn her up with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put it into their hearts to carry out His purpose, and to carry out a common purpose and to give their kingdom to the Wild Beast until God's words have come to pass.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman whom you have seen is the great city which has kingly power over the kings of the earth.«
B066C018V001	66	18	1	After these things I saw another angel coming down from Heaven, armed with great power. The earth shone with his splendor,
B066C018V002	66	18	2	and with a mighty voice he cried out, saying, »Great Babylon has fallen, has fallen, and has become a home for demons and a stronghold for every kind of foul spirit and for every kind of foul and hateful bird.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all the nations have drunk the wine of the anger provoked by her fornication, and the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth have grown rich through her excessive luxury.«
B066C018V004	66	18	4	Then I heard another voice from Heaven, which said, »Come out of her, My people, that you may not become partakers in her sins, nor receive a share of her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins are piled up to the sky, and God has called to mind her unrighteous deeds.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Give back to her as she has given; repay her in accordance with her doings, twice as much; in the bowl that she has mixed, mix twice as much for her.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	She has freely glorified herself and revelled in luxury; equally freely administer torment to her, and woe. For in her heart she boasts, saying, `I sit enthroned as Queen: no widow am I: I shall never know sorrow.'
B066C018V008	66	18	8	»For this reason calamities shall come thick upon her on a single day –death and sorrow and famine– and she shall be burned to the ground. For strong is the Lord God who has judged her.«
B066C018V009	66	18	9	The kings of the earth who have committed fornication with her, and have revelled in luxury, shall weep aloud and lament over her when they see the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	while they stand afar off because of their terror at her heavy punishment, and say, `Alas, alas, thou great city, O Babylon, the mighty city! For in one short hour thy doom has come!'
B066C018V011	66	18	11	And the merchants of the earth weep aloud and lament over her, because now there is no sale for their cargoes–
B066C018V012	66	18	12	cargoes of gold and silver, of jewels and pearls, of fine linen, purple and silk, and of scarlet stuff; all kinds of rare woods, and all kinds of goods in ivory and in very costly wood, in bronze, steel and marble.
B066C018V013	66	18	13	Also cinnamon and amomum; odors to burn as incense or for perfume; frankincense, wine, oil; fine flour, wheat, cattle and sheep; horses and carriages and slaves; and the lives of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	The dainties that thy soul longed for are gone from thee, and all thine elegance and splendor have perished, and never again shall they be found.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	Those who traded in these things, who grew wealthy through her, will stand afar off, struck with terror at her punishment,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	weeping aloud and sorrowing, and saying, `Alas, alas, for this great city, which was brilliantly arrayed in fine linen, and purple and scarlet stuff, and beautified with gold, jewels and pearls;
B066C018V017	66	18	17	because in one short hour all this great wealth has been laid waste!' And every shipmaster and every passenger by sea and the crews and all who ply their trade on the sea,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	stood afar off, and cried aloud when they saw the smoke of her burning. And they said, `What city is like this great city?'
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they threw dust upon their heads, and cried out, weeping aloud and sorrowing. `Alas, alas,' they said, `for this great city, in which, through her vast wealth, the owners of all the ships on the sea have grown rich; because in one short hour she has been laid waste!'
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, O Heaven, and you saints and Apostles and Prophets; for God has taken vengeance upon her because of you.«
B066C018V021	66	18	21	Then a single angel of great strength took a stone which resembled a huge millstone, and hurled it into the sea, saying, »So shall Babylon, that great city, be violently hurled down and never again be found.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	No harp or song, no flute or trumpet, shall ever again be heard in thee; no craftsman of any kind shall ever again be found in thee; nor shall the grinding of the mill ever again be heard in thee.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	Never again shall the light of a lamp shine in thee, and never again shall the voice of a bridegroom or of a bride be heard in thee. For thy merchants were the great men of the earth, and with the magic which thou didst practise all nations were led astray.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of Prophets and of God's people and of all who had been put to death on the earth.«
B066C019V001	66	19	1	After this I seemed to hear the far-echoing voices of a great multitude in Heaven, who said, »Hallelujah! The salvation and the glory and the power belong to our God.
B066C019V002	66	19	2	True and just are His judgments, because He has judged the great Harlot who was corrupting the whole earth with her fornication, and He has taken vengeance for the blood of His bondservants which her hands have shed.«
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And a second time they said, »Hallelujah! For her smoke ascends until the Ages of the Ages.«
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the twenty-four Elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshipped God who sits upon the throne. »Even so,« they said; »Hallelujah!«
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And from the throne there came a voice which said, »Praise our God, all you His bondservants–you who fear Him, both the small and the great.«
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I seemed to hear the voices of a great multitude and the sound of many waters and of loud peals of thunder, which said, »Hallelujah! Because the Lord our God, the Ruler of all, has become King.
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice and triumph and give Him the glory; for the time for the marriage of the Lamb has come, and His Bride has made herself ready.«
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And she was permitted to array herself in fine linen, shining and spotless; the fine linen being the righteous actions of God's people.
B066C019V009	66	19	9	And he said to me, »Write as follows: `Blessed are those who receive an invitation to the Marriage Supper of the Lamb.'« And he added, still addressing me, »These are truly the words of God.«
B066C019V010	66	19	10	Then I fell at his feet to worship him. But he exclaimed, »Oh, do not do that. I am a fellow bondservant of yours and a fellow bondservant of your brethren who have borne testimony to Jesus. Worship God.« Testimony to Jesus is the spirit which underlies Prophecy.
B066C019V011	66	19	11	Then I saw a door open in Heaven, and a white horse appeared. Its rider was named »Faithful and True« –being One who in righteousness acts as Judge, and makes war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	His eyes were like a flame of fire, and on His head were many kingly crowns; and He has a name written upon Him which no one but He Himself knows.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	The outer garment in which He is clad has been dipped in blood and His name is THE WORD OF GOD.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	The armies in Heaven followed Him–mounted on white horses and clothed in fine linen, white and spotless.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	From His mouth there comes a sharp sword with which He will smite the nations; and He will Himself be their Shepherd, ruling them with a scepter of iron; and it is His work to tread the winepress of the fierce anger of God, the Ruler of all.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	And on His outer garment and on His thigh He has a name written, KING OF KINGS AND LORD OF LORDS.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	And I saw a single angel standing in the full light of the sun, who cried in a loud voice to all the birds that flew across the sky, »Come and be present at God's great supper,
B066C019V018	66	19	18	that you may feast on the flesh of kings and the flesh of generals and the flesh of mighty men, on the flesh of horses and their riders, and on the flesh of all mankind, whether they are free men or slaves, great men or small.«
B066C019V019	66	19	19	And I saw the Wild Beast, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, all assembled to make war, once for all, against the Rider upon the horse and against His army. And the Wild Beast was captured, and with him the false Prophet
B066C019V020	66	19	20	who had done the miracles in his presence with which he had led astray those who had received the mark of the Wild Beast, and those who worshipped his statue. Both of them were thrown alive into the Lake of fire that was all ablaze with sulphur.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	But the rest were killed with the sword that came from the mouth of the Rider on the horse. And the birds all fed ravenously upon their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	Then I saw an angel coming down from Heaven, having the key of the bottomless pit, and upon his arm he carried a great chain.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	He laid hold of the Dragon –the ancient serpent– who is the Devil and the Adversary, and bound him for a thousand years, and hurled him into the bottomless pit.
B066C020V003	66	20	3	He closed the entrance and put a seal upon him in order that he might be unable to lead the nations astray any more until the thousand years were at an end. Afterwards he is to be set at liberty for a short time.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	And I saw thrones, and some who were seated on them, to whom judgment was entrusted. And I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded on account of the testimony that they had borne to Jesus and on account of God's Message, and also the souls of those who had not worshipped the Wild Beast or his statue, nor received his mark on their foreheads or on their hands; and they came to Life and were kings with Christ for a thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	No one else who was dead rose to Life until the thousand years were at an end. This is the First Resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	Blessed and holy are those who share in the First Resurrection. The Second Death has no power over them, but they shall be priests to God and to Christ, and shall be kings with Christ for the thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	But when the thousand years are at an end, the Adversary will be released from his imprisonment,
B066C020V008	66	20	8	and will go out to lead astray the nations in all the four corners of the earth, Gog and Magog, and assemble them for war, and they are like the sands on the seashore in number.
B066C020V009	66	20	9	And they went up over the whole breadth of the earth and surrounded the encampment of God's people and the beloved city. But fire came down from Heaven and consumed them;
B066C020V010	66	20	10	and the Devil, who had been leading them astray, was thrown into the Lake of fire and sulphur where the Wild Beast and the false Prophet were, and day and night they will suffer torture until the Ages of the Ages.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	Then I saw a great white throne and One who was seated on it, from whose presence earth and sky fled away, and no place was found for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	And I saw the dead, the great and the small, standing in front of the throne. And books were opened; and so was another book–namely, the Book of Life; and the dead were judged by the things recorded in the books in accordance with what their conduct had been.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	Then the sea yielded up the dead who were in it, Death and Hades yielded up the dead who were in them, and each man was judged in accordance with what his conduct had been.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	Then Death and Hades were thrown into the Lake of fire; this is the Second Death–the Lake of fire.
B066C020V015	66	20	15	And if any one's name was not found recorded in the Book of Life he was thrown into the Lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	And I saw a new Heaven and a new earth; for the first Heaven and the first earth were gone, and the sea no longer exists.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	And I saw the holy city, the new Jerusalem, coming down out of Heaven from God and made ready like a bride attired to meet her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a loud voice, which came from the throne, say, »God's dwelling place is among men and He will dwell among them and they shall be His peoples. Yes, God Himself will be among them.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	He will wipe every tear from their eyes. Death shall be no more; nor sorrow, nor wail of woe, nor pain; for the first things have passed away.«
B066C021V005	66	21	5	Then He who was seated on the throne said, »I am re-creating all things.« And He added, »Write down these words, for they are trustworthy and true.«
B066C021V006	66	21	6	He also said, »They have now been fulfilled. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the End. To those who are thirsty I will give the privilege of drinking from the well of the Water of Life without payment.
B066C021V007	66	21	7	All this shall be the heritage of him who overcomes, and I will be his God and he shall be one of My sons.
B066C021V008	66	21	8	But as for cowards and the unfaithful, and the polluted, and murderers, fornicators, and those who practise magic or worship idols, and all liars–the portion allotted to them shall be in the Lake which burns with fire and sulphur. This is the Second Death.«
B066C021V009	66	21	9	Then there came one of the seven angels who were carrying the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues. »Come with me,« he said, »and I will show you the Bride, the Lamb's wife.«
B066C021V010	66	21	10	So in the Spirit he carried me to the top of a vast, lofty mountain, and showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, coming down out of Heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	and bringing with it the glory of God. It shone with a radiance like that of a very precious stone–such as a jasper, bright and transparent.
B066C021V012	66	21	12	It has a wall, massive and high, with twelve large gates, and in charge of the gates were twelve angels. And overhead, above the gates, names were inscribed which are those of the twelve tribes of the descendants of Israel.
B066C021V013	66	21	13	There were three gates on the east, three on the north, three on the south, and three on the west.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	The wall of the city had twelve foundation stones, and engraved upon them were twelve names–the names of the twelve Apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	Now he who was speaking to me had a measuring-rod of gold, with which to measure the city and its gates and its wall.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	The plan of the city is a square, the length being the same as the breadth; and he measured the city furlong by furlong, with his measuring rod–it is twelve hundred miles long, and the length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured the wall of it–a wall of a hundred and forty-four cubits, according to human measure, which was also that of the angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	The solid fabric of the wall was jasper; and the city itself was made of gold, resembling transparent glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	As for the foundation-stones of the city wall, which were beautified with various kinds of precious stones, the first was jasper, the second sapphire, the third chalcedony, the fourth emerald, the fifth sardonyx, the sixth sardius,
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth, the twelfth amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates were twelve pearls; each of them consisting of a single pearl. And the main street of the city was made of pure gold, resembling transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	I saw no sanctuary in the city, for the Lord God, the Ruler of all, is its Sanctuary, and so is the Lamb.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	Nor has the city any need of the sun or of the moon, to give it light; for the glory of God has shone upon it and its lamp is the Lamb.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	The nations will live their lives by its light; and the kings of the earth are to bring their glory into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And in the daytime (for there will be no night there) the gates will never be closed;
B066C021V026	66	21	26	and the glory and honor of the nations shall be brought into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	And no unclean thing shall ever enter it, nor any one who is guilty of base conduct or tells lies, but only they whose names stand recorded in the Lamb's Book of Life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	Then he showed me the river of the Water of Life, bright as crystal, issuing from the throne of God and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	On either side of the river, midway between it and the main street of the city, was the Tree of Life. It produced twelve kinds of fruit, yielding a fresh crop month by month, and the leaves of the tree served as medicine for the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	»In future there will be no curse,« he said, »but the throne of God and of the Lamb will be in that city. And His servants will render Him holy service and will see His face,
B066C022V004	66	22	4	and His name will be on their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And there will be no night there; and they have no need of lamplight or sunlight, for the Lord God will shine upon them, and they will be kings until the Ages of the Ages.«
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said to me, »These words are trustworthy and true; and the Lord, the God of the spirits of the Prophets, sent His angel to make known to His servants the things which must soon happen.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	`I am coming quickly.' Blessed is he who is mindful of the predictions contained in this book.«
B066C022V008	66	22	8	I John heard and saw these things; and when I had heard and seen them, I fell at the feet of the angel who was showing me them–to worship him.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	But he said to me, »Oh, do not do that. I am a fellow bondservant of yours, and a fellow bondservant of your brethren the Prophets and of those who are mindful of the teachings of this book. Worship God.«
B066C022V010	66	22	10	»Make no secret,« he added, »of the meaning of the predictions contained in this book; for the time for their fulfillment is now close at hand.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	Let the dishonest man act dishonestly still; let the filthy make himself filthy still; let the righteous practise righteousness still; and let the holy be made holy still.«
B066C022V012	66	22	12	»I am coming quickly; and My reward is with Me, that I may requite every man in accordance with what his conduct has been.
B066C022V013	66	22	13	I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.«
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are those who wash their robes clean, that they may have a right to the Tree of Life, and may go through the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	The unclean are shut out, and so are all who practise magic, all fornicators, all murderers, and those who worship idols, and every one who loves falsehood and tells lies.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	»I Jesus have sent My angel for him solemnly to declare these things to you among the Churches. I am the Root and the offspring of David, the bright Morning Star.«
B066C022V017	66	22	17	The Spirit and the Bride say, `Come;' and whoever hears, let him say, `Come;' and let those who are thirsty come. Whoever will, let him take the Water of Life, without payment.
B066C022V018	66	22	18	»I solemnly declare to every one who hears the words of the prophecy contained in this book, that if any one adds to those words, God will add to him the plagues spoken of in this book;«
B066C022V019	66	22	19	and that if any one takes away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God will take from him his share in the Tree of Life and in the holy city–the things described in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	»He who solemnly declares all this says,« `Yes, I am coming quickly.' Amen. Come, Lord Jesus.
B066C022V021	66	22	21	The grace of the Lord Jesus be with God's people.
